title: easy no-knead bread(very good)
directions: (Generously use cooking spray at the bottom of your baking pan.)

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Serve with bite-sized vegetables.

title: luba's raspberry sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook in boiling water until soft. Mash potatoes; add butter, brown sugar and milk and mix.
(Can be made ahead of time up to this point and refrigerated.)
Put in a 350° oven to heat, covered, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Last 10 minutes put raspberries (defrosted) on top; cover and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes (until raspberries are warm).

title: roasted georgia pecans
directions: Roast pecans in microwave in a flat microwave dish for 4 minutes.
Let stand for 1 minute, then roast for 2 more minutes. Stir in butter and mix around until all pecans are coated.
Add salt and stir again until pecans are evenly coated.
Serve.

title: pickled green peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Remove seed pods and white "seams."
Cut lengthwise into 3/4-inch strips.
Place pepper strips in bowl. Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes and drain.
Combine vinegar, water and sugar in saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes. Meanwhile, pack peppers into clean, hot jars.
To each jar add 2 cloves garlic or 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon of garlic powder or salt to your own taste.
Pour hot liquid over peppers to within 1/2 inch of top, making sure vinegar solution covers pepper.
Cap each jar at once.
Process 5 minutes in boiling-water bath.
Makes 4 pints.

title: quick and easy crab soup
directions: Parboil potatoes.
Add 1 can water to each can of soup.
Bring soup to boil; add Old Bay, crab and potatoes.
Simmer about 1/2 hour or more.

title: cheese log
directions: Using a rolling pin, spread Velveeta cheese on wax paper (I put wax paper on both top and bottom to spread out cheese). Cheese should be about 12 inches long, nearly as wide as the paper, and 1/2 inch thick.
Remove top sheet of wax paper and spread on cream cheese.
Mix olives and chili peppers together and spread on top of cream cheese.
Form a "log" by folding the cheese in thirds.
Cover with clean wax paper.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Can be cut in half to make 2 logs.
Great with Ritz crackers.

title: crostata italiana
directions: Mix ingredients for dough; reserve part for top crust.
Roll out dough and line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sliced apples, peaches, pears, pineapple and raisins over crust.
Sprinkle nuts over fruit.
Roll out remaining dough and cut into strips.
Crisscross strips over fruit filling.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: county fair broccoli
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; stir in onion, broccoli and cheese.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until set. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buffalo chips(cookies)
directions: Using a large bowl, blend butter and sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Sift salt, flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add to bowl; mix well.
Stir in oats, corn flakes, chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Use an ice cream scoop to place 6 cookies on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cookies will be soft and chewy if you don't bake until brown. Makes about 36 very large cookies.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding in bowl.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix in fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Red layers:
Dissolve Jell-O and granulated sugar in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and lemon juice.
Stir until berries thaw.
Chill in bowl until partially set.

title: chicken casserole for a crowd
directions: Line two baking dishes with butter and bread.
Spread chicken over bread.
Cut up chestnuts and mushrooms.
Dot with mayonnaise. Combine soups.
Add pimento and top with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over mixture.
Keep in refrigerator 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Saute butter and bread crumbs until brown. Spread over mixture.
Bake for 15 more minutes.
Number of Servings:

title: toffee nut bar
directions: Mix together.
Press and flatten with hand to cover bottom ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven. Remove from oven and spread with topping.
Return to oven 25 minutes.
Cool slightly. Cut into bars.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen 1 x 3-inch bars.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat yolks; set aside.
Boil noodles; drain.
Mix egg yolks, cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, butter, sugar and salt until well blended with electric mixer.
Add noodles and blend.
Add egg whites and fold in gently.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish.

title: yorkshire pudding(served with roast beef dinner)
directions: Be sure all ingredients are at room temperature or they will not puff.

title: granny's orange jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix together jello, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add fruit and sit together.
Quick, easy, good!

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Mix and press into greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water and set aside to cool. Whip the mayonnaise with a mixer until fluffy. Stir in milk, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a mold and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup of the yellow cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, margarine or butter and beaten egg.
Stir by hand until mixture is crumbly.
Press the mixture evenly over bottom and 1 inch up the sides of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: topknots
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add eggs, flour, salt and butter.
Will form a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead.
Put back into bowl; let rise.
Punch down.
Knead. Roll until thin.
Spread with butter.
Roll up (jelly roll style). Cut in 1-inch slices.
Place in greased muffin tin; let rise. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook soup with onion using 1/2 cup of water.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain broccoli and mix with soup mixture. Add cooked rice and Cheez Whiz; pour in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is bubbly.

title: appetizer fast with cream cheese
directions: With softened cream cheese (put in a pretty dish), drizzle mango chutney throughout; top with almonds.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable main dish(north africa)
directions: Put
oil
into	large skillet which can be tightly covered. Add
onions and brown lightly.
Add vegetables in order of	 their cooking,
i.e.
peppers,
eggplant,
tomatoes
and greens.
Add sugar, pepper, salt and seasoning at this point. There
will be plenty of broth.
Cover tightly and cook slowly until vegetables are almost tender.	After removing cover, use large
spoon	to make wells on top of mixture.
Break one egg for each person; cover tightly and poach eggs.

title: baked pancake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in 10 to 12-inch skillet (preferably cast-iron variety).
Combine flour and milk; beat lightly (okay if lumpy).
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into skillet.
(Recipe turns out best if butter is still quite warm.) Sprinkle with nutmeg lightly.
Place in heated oven.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Recipe should rise around edges and puff slightly in middle.
Serve immediately sprinkled with powdered sugar.
May squeeze lemon or serve with jam.
Serves 2.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add egg, milk and oil, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in the nuts.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle tops with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Add Eagle Brand milk, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix together and add bananas.
Top with vanilla wafers.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Separate dough into long rectangles.
Place them in an ungreased 15 x 10-inch baking pan; press over bottom and sides. Seal perforations.
Bake until golden, around 15 to 18 minutes. Cool completely.
Blend next 6 ingredients until smooth.
Spread evenly over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into appetizer sized pieces.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 60 pieces.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in flour, cherries and pecans.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour sauce over carrots and let stand for a short time.
Serve hot.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: oyster pie
directions: Simmer garlic in melted butter about 5 minutes before adding flour and browning.
Add seasoning and oysters.
Let oysters cook in roux about 5 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Season well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Cover bottom of oblong baking dish with dried beef.
Arrange unsalted chicken on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Place 1/2 slice bacon on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 225° for 4 hours.
Cover dish with foil.
You can use all chicken parts in place of breast.

title: roast venison
directions: Soak fresh or frozen venison to stand overnight in marinade in the refrigerator.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour and brown in hot skillet.
Place in crock-pot all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: gorgeous jello
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
When completely dissolved, add ice cream.
Mix well and chill.
Decorate with mandarin oranges or other fruit.
Kids love it plain, too!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix nacho cheese, sour cream and mayo and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle taco seasoning over mixture.
Add chopped onion, lettuce, tomato, black olives and cheese.
Serve with tostado chips.

title: seafood pasta sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Pour in wine and cook 2 minutes.
Chop tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and their juices, basil, oregano and parsley.
Cook on medium-high heat for 5 minutes, then reduce to a simmer.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add seafoods.
Cover and cook until seafood is just firm, about 3 minutes.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Add pepper to taste.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald, peel and slice the tomatoes.
Peel and slice real fine the onions.
Sprinkle the tomatoes and onions with salt.
Bring tomatoes, onions and peppers to a boil in the vinegar.
Add brown sugar and cook until thick then add the spices.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Rinse meat; pat dry.
Trim off fat; season lightly with Adolph's seasoning or salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Place carrots and onion in crock-pot; lay meat on top.
Pour stewed tomatoes on top of meat.
Mix in 1 tablespoon sugar with tomato sauce.
Pour over meat mixture; cover.
Cook for 10 to 11 hours on slow or 5 to 6 hours on high until tender.
Add a little bit of cornstarch with water to thicken sauce if not thick enough.
Serve over mashed potatoes or noodles.
Add bouillon cube to sauce in crock-pot.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat on top of stove.
Mix all other ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Stir in browned meat.
Simmer for 1 hour. Add more water if necessary as it cooks.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut steak into 1-inch pieces.
Place steak in a 3-quart casserole or Dutch oven coated with vegetable cooking spray.

title: children's casserole delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered 1-quart casserole dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and cool.
Mix macaroni, shrimp, celery and onion together.
Stir in mayonnaise and Old Bay seasoning to your own taste.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish in lightly greased baking dish.
Squeeze lemon juice over fish.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar on fish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until flaky.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of the bacon.
Arrange dried beef in 9 x 13 pan.
Place the chicken on dried beef. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.
6 to 8 servings.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skins are tough; otherwise, just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes in thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use the handle of a wooden spoon lying parallel to potato to keep from cutting all the way through.
Place potatoes in microsafe dish.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley, chives or sage.
Microwave on High power for 10 minutes, rearranging potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave at High power another 4 to 6 minutes, until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: oreo cake
directions: First Layer:
Crush Oreo cookies and mix with melted margarine in 13 x 9-inch glass dish to form a crust.

title: pam's lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna.
Cook sausage, ground beef, onion and garlic in large skillet over medium heat until sausage is not pink and onion is tender.
Drain and stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, basil, fennel seed and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
In a bowl, blend Ricotta, egg, parsley and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt. Place sauce, then lasagna, then Parmesan cheese in 3 layers, alternating in that order.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Uncover, then bake for 20 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: summer squash and plum tomatoes
directions: Cut up vegetables and layer into microwavable dish.
Drizzle liberally with Caesar salad dressing. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese to taste. Microwave on High for 8 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry victory
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in baking dish for bottom layer. Blend rest of ingredients and spread for second layer.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: christmas kraut
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover.
Put in refrigerator. Let set overnight.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add flour, corn, butter, milk and seasonings.
Pour into casserole dish and cover.
Bake 45 minutes in preheated 400° oven.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well, add one egg at a time, mixing well after each.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours or until it tests done.
Don't open oven for one hour.

title: squash medley
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Add a little water and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: potato candy ala soliday
directions: Mash potato with vanilla.
Add enough powdered sugar to dough to make stiff to roll.
Roll to 1/2 to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up like jelly roll.
Let dry and cut into slices 1/2-inch thick.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Gently mix by hand Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Add frozen lemonade and stir until well blended.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan; stir until blended and spread evenly in pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples with sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Lay apples in 8-inch buttered pan.
Mix brown sugar, butter and flour.
Spread on top of apples.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: banana snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine sugar, margarine and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in buttermilk, bananas and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: sparkling strawberry punch
directions: In covered blender at high speed, blend strawberries and undiluted lemonade until they are thoroughly blended.
Pour mixture into large punch bowl; stir until sugar dissolves. Garnish with orange slices and fresh strawberries.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine, pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients, press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done.
Remove skin and bones.
Tear chicken in bite-size pieces and place in long baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top, then dot with butter.
Bake until bubbly and brown at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: margret's colorado pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all the margarine into a 9 x 13-inch glass or metal pan and put in oven until the margarine melts.

title: angelic chicken and shrimp
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Brown lightly in margarine in skillet.
Remove to 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add mushrooms to drippings in skillet.
Saute until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth.
Simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in chives, tomato paste, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add wine.
Spoon over chicken in baking dish.
Chill until baking time.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 20 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes longer. Serve with hot cooked rice and a green vegetable.
Serves 8.

title: potato potachelli
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Cool potatoes well; cut into chunks.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and fettuccine casserole
directions: Melt butter and flour together, stirring constantly.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Continue stirring, and cook until thickened. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Put into buttered casserole and top with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add 2 cups bran cereal to the boiling water.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar in large bowl of mixer.
Add eggs; beat well. Add buttermilk and scalded bran cereal.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add dry ingredients to liquid mixture.
You will have to transfer to larger bowl when adding dry ingredients. Stir in remaining bran cereal and raisins.
Bake in greased muffin tins for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° to 400° oven.

title: grapefruit and apple mist
directions: Stir juices and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Gradually stir in ginger ale.
Serve with crushed ice.
Makes approximately 5 cups.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk and boil 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter, cocoa, oatmeal and vanilla. Mix together and drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: 7-up baked ham
directions: Wash and score ham.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange pineapple slices on top of ham; secure with whole cloves, also placing on ham.
Place cherries in pineapple holes.
In bowl, mix 7-Up and sugar until dissolved.
Pour in 7-Up and pour all over ham.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or heated thoroughly.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Heat bacon in oven only until limp.
Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Chop bacon and beef over chicken.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at only 200° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Saute mushrooms in butter at medium temperature for about 8 minutes.
Scatter mushrooms over top of chicken.
Sprinkle parsley over all.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain any grease.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and stir.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: hot dip
directions: Melt all ingredients together and serve with nacho chips.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, cream cheese and flavorings until light and fluffy.
Separate eggs and drop, one yolk at a time, into mixture while continuing to beat.
Add cake flour gradually, beating well.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form and fold into batter.
Bake at 325°.

title: chocolate rolls
directions: Mix everything, but chocolate chips.
Roll into 2-inch logs. Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler layer pan.
Dip logs in this mixture and place on wax paper.

title: crab shell
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place in buttered dish or individual shell dishes (or spray with Pam).
Crush Pepperidge Farm and put on top of mixture.
Add melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water 15 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Combine next 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well.
Stir in potatoes.
Spoon mixture in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with green onion, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: red rooster stew
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones.
In large pot, add all ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer on low for 20 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: cracklin' bran sweet potato bake
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer, combine potatoes, 4 tablespoons butter, juice, sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth. Stir in 1 cup of the marshmallows; spread in 1 1/2 quart glass baking dish.
Top with the remaining marshmallows.
Melt remaining butter.
Combine with cereal.
Sprinkle over marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: baked oysters
directions: Roll oysters in flour, then in egg, then in cracker crumbs, then in oil.
Drain for a few minutes. Bake in a 400° oven until browned.

title: maurice salad dressing
directions: Mix with wire whip until well blended.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together Cheddar cheese, butter, chicken soup, sour cream and onion.
Pour over potatoes, slightly stir.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with 4 cups crushed corn flakes and 1 stick butter (mixed together).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: Crush 1 1/2 packages of cookies. Melt the butter.
Mix and press into the bottom of a freezable large container.
Spread the ice cream (softened) over this crust.
Next, put a layer of crushed cookies. Top with the hot fudge topping.
Freeze for 3 hours.
Remove from freezer.
Spread with the Cool Whip and sprinkle with the cookies left.
Cut and serve.

title: snow's "anniversary salad"
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Cool.
Mix Jell-O with marshmallows, diced bananas and pineapple.
Set in refrigerator to congeal.
Mix together pineapple juice, flour, beaten egg, sugar, margarine and salt.
Cook this mixture until thick.
Cool.
To this cooled mixture add softened cream cheese.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold cream cheese mixture into cream.
Spread on top of Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top and refrigerate.

title: kurt's clay
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a pan, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and continue cooking until mixture reaches a soft dough consistency.
Remove from heat, cool and then knead.
Clay will dry hard overnight.

title: thanksgiving apple salad(serves 8)
directions: Stir together the sugar and flour. Whisk in the cream. Pour the cream mixture into a heavy non-aluminum saucepan. Continue mixing. Add the pineapple and cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until the mixture thickens. Add the butter; remove the pan from the heat and let the mixture cool. When cooled, add the apples, nuts and cherries and mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: crunchy cabbage salad
directions: Toss together first 4 ingredients. Crunch dry noodles and add to cabbage mixture.
Reserve seasonings for dressing.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper and add Ramen seasonings and mix well.
Just before serving, add dressing to cabbage mixture and toss well.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water to rolling boil; slowly stir in grits.
Cook and stir over medium heat until grits have thickened, 3 to 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients to hot grits, mixing well.
Turn into greased, shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Melt butter or oleo in top of double boiler.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute over direct heat.
Add cooked shrimp, grated American cheese and cocktail sauce.
Cook over hot water until cheese melts, stirring often.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Shape into balls and brown in hot salad oil.
When meatballs are brown, remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Stir 4 tablespoons flour into the far left in pan and add consomme and bottled sauce; cook until thick.
Add sherry or Burgundy and pour over meatballs.
At this point, they may be frozen or out in the refrigerator for later use.
When ready to serve, heat for about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: emma ame's salmon macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni;	add 1/2 in buttered casserole.	Add 1/2 salmon, then the other half of macaroni and salmon; pour cream of chicken soup
over	all.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs. Bake.

title: favorite corn pudding
directions: Stir ingredients together. Pour into small casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix everything except the 1/4 cup pecans.
Roll the ingredients into a ball.
Roll ball in the 1/4 cup pecans.
Keeps well in freezer.
Can also be used as a spread.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Place mixture in a 9-inch square pan.
Spread evenly.
Cover top with lettuce.
Place tomatoes and olives atop that.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate. Serve with taco chips.

title: beets in honey sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and salt.
Blend in water or beet juice.
Add vinegar, honey and margarine.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: oatmeal-cherry chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use shortening or cooking spray to grease cookie sheets.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange peaches in bottom of 9-inch pan.
Combine cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Mix flour, egg, baking powder, salt and remaining sugar and cinnamon until moist.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Melt butter and drizzle over peach mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom's barbecue chicken wings
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and Tabasco in a pot and heat until melted.
Place wings in large baking pan and cook in oven at 350° to 375° until fat is rendered.
Remove from oven and drain off all fat, about 1 hour.
Pour sauce over wings; return to oven and bake until crisp.
Sprinkle Ranch mix over all and bake another 10 minutes.

title: wild rice and chicken breasts
directions: Place wild rice in buttered baking dish.
Combine water, soup, sour cream, wine and mushrooms.
Pour half of mixture over wild rice.
Place chicken on top and pour over remaining soup mixture. Season to taste.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix batter and pour into greased baking dish.
Put 1/2 cup butter over batter.
Add 1 1/2 cups mashed peaches (sweetened). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix everything together and let stand in refrigerator at least 6 hours (overnight is best).

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve cream cheese and jello with boiling water using a wire whisk. Add 7-up. Pour into jello mold. refrigerate.

title: zucchini-carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until frothy.
Gradually beat in oil. Add dry ingredients.
Beat at high speed 4 minutes.
Stir in carrots, zucchini and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise together and spread over the top of the peas.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Toss, then serve.

title: pretend soup
directions: Place orange juice in bowl.
Add yogurt, honey and lemon juice.
Whisk together.
In each bowl, add 5 slices banana and 2 tablespoons strawberries.
Ladle soup and eat!

title: apple squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening as for pastry.
Beat 2 egg yolks in a cup and add milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Roll half of dough; put in slightly greased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cornflakes on the crust.
Slice the apples and place them on the cornflakes.
Sprinkle rest of cornflakes, sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Dot with a few pats of oleo.
Cover with the rest of rolled pastry.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and spread over crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
While still warm, dribble with small amount of powdered sugar frosting.
When cool, cut into squares.
May use other fresh fruit.

title: applesauce chicken
directions: Combine mustard and brown sugar.
Roll each chicken piece in mixture and place in large greased baking dish.
Sprinkle garlic, salt and pepper on top.
Pour applesauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and bake in an ungreased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: doggie biscuits(really for dogs)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.
On lightly floured surface, use a floured rolling pin to roll out dough to 1/8-inch thick.
Use 2-inch heart cookie cutter, or smaller, for smaller dogs.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until firm.
Cool on wire rack completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until it spins a thread.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add vanilla.
Then mix with sugar and Karo mixture.
Spoon out on foil.

title: christmas smell
directions: Cut all ingredients up fine; add 2 cups of water and let simmer in a coffeepot or saucepan.
When water evaporates, add more.

title: baked chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with the rice.
Top with chicken.
Mix water and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Top with dry onion soup.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake 30 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: big affair punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Chill syrup and juices 2 to 3 hours.
Strain, if desired. Add cherries and juice, water and ginger ale. Pour over block of ice in punch bowl.
Makes 75 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda, white sugar and salt.
Mix Wesson oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
When well mixed, add nuts and raisins.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
This makes 3 (9-inch) loaves.

title: pork basting sauce
directions: Baste pork frequently while cooking.
Pour excess sauce over meat before serving.

title: copper pennies
directions: Make dressing from Miracle Whip, sugar and milk.
Whip together; again, amounts used will depend on how many vegetables you use.
Pour dressing over vegetables and chill.
Sometimes I add pepper to dressing.

title: shrimp and artichoke pasta
directions: Saute garlic in butter until soft.
Add shrimp along with remaining ingredients except spaghetti and Parmesan.
Saute over low heat until shrimp turns pink, approximately 6 to 8 minutes. Serve over spaghetti noodles.
Sprinkle with fresh Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken breasts with wine
directions: Dip cutlets in flour, beaten egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry. Remove cutlets and place in baking pan.
Saute onions and remove. Saute mushrooms and remove.
Mix wine, broth and onions.
Pour over cutlets.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Ten minutes before end of baking time, spread mushrooms and grapes over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes longer.

title: tabbouli salad
directions: Place in an 8-cup glass measure 2 cups water.
Microcook on High for 6 minutes until boils.
Add 1 cup cracked wheat bulgur. Stand, covered, 1 hour.
Drain excess liquid.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken & dumplings the way mandy would make them(dedicated to my mom, mandy clemons)
directions: Mix together flour & oil.
Stir in some milk until dough is like biscuit dough.
Flour surface of table or board, and put dough on it.
(I have a table cloth my mother used that I put the flour on.)

title: golden apple sour cream muffins
directions: Combine sour cream, egg, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and allspice.
Stir into sour cream mixture.
Fold in raisins and apples.
Spoon evenly into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: tea cakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine softened butter and sugar.
Mix well. Add eggs; stir until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll out in small balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Take a medium drinking glass and dip the bottom in flour.
Press down cookies with glass.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces and roll in cornstarch. Fry in hot oil until brown.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Add remaining ingredients except soy sauce and cook for 10 minutes. Add soy sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Simmer bourbon, brown sugar and ketchup in saucepan on stove for 1 hour, uncovered.
Put into crock-pot and add hot dogs. Cut into quarters.
Cover and simmer.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain excess grease.
Add tomato sauce and beans and cook 5 to 10 more minutes.
Spread rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stick in oven until soft.
Mix eggs and half of cheese; pour over rolls.
Spread hamburger mixture over eggs; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or desired brownness.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and oleo to boiling.
Add flour all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is very thick and forms a ball that follows spoon round.
Remove from heat.
Add large eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until dough is smooth and shiny.
Spoon 8 high mounds on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 40 minutes until puffed and golden brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: for arthritis
directions: Pour out 2 ounces
of
alcohol	and pour in the wintergreen. Add the aspirins.
Shake
well
and
rub
... and have someone there to catch you!

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
Combine fruit and nuts in large bowl.
Toss.
Combine pudding and juice in mixing bowl; beat at high speed for 1 minute.
Pour mix over fruit and nuts; stir gently.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: margarita mousse
directions: Dip rims of 4 to 6 dessert glasses in lime juice; then dip in sugar and let dry.
Combine Cool Whip, milk, liqueur, blending well.
Dissolve Jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping mixture and spoon into glasses.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Garnish with lime twists, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: gobbler's chili
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground turkey, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Drain.
Stir undrained beans, undrained tomatoes, brown sugar, salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ladle into bowls.
Top with shredded cheese, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: open face turkey sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread and cheese.
In broiler, toast one side of bread.
On untoasted side, place 1/4 of turkey mixture on each slice of bread.
Return to broiler until bread begins to brown.
Remove and place cheese on top of turkey mixture.
Return to broiler until cheese is melted.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Boil all ingredients together in heavy skillet until water disappears and nuts are sugary.
Pour out on cookie sheet and separate.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over
Jell-O
and stir until dissolved. Add
salt
and
white
vinegar.
Chill
until mixture begins
to thicken.
Beat with mixer until mixture is foamy, 2 to
3 minutes.
Fold
in
or beat at low speed with mixer the sour cream
and
mayonnaise.
Add
cucumber and onion, mixing thoroughly.
Place in well-greased 2 quart mold or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Garnish with cucumber slices so guests won't mistake it for lime dessert.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into cupcake paper and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together in microwave.
Spray pan with Pam or butter.
Line with pecans.
Pour caramels over top and cool.
Cut in squares, then melt barks together.
Dip squares in bark.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, lemon juice, crushed pineapple, ground cranberries and chopped nuts; mix well.
Chill until set.

title: green tomato relish(sandwich spread)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mix well and put in bag to drain overnight.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes.
Put into hot sterilized jars and seal with lids or cool.
When lukewarm, add mustard and salad dressing.
Mix and fill in jars.
Will keep without sealing if refrigerated.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple and bring to a boil.
Cool completely. Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip and add to cooled jello mixture.

title: cheese and mushroom potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes and cook until tender.
In a casserole dish, place
a
layer
of
potatoes,
then a layer of cheese. Squeeze butter over this.
Add another layer of potatoes, more cheese
and butter.
Pour can of soup over this.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, combine the first four ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Set aside.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
You may add a few maraschino cherries, if you wish.

title: waldorf astoria red cake
directions: Sift together salt and flour.
Make paste of coloring and cocoa.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to vinegar in measuring cup, it foams, then blend into cake mixture.
Bake in three 8-inch pans (greased) at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with frosting.

title: corn and celery soup
directions: Simmer the corn in milk until tender. Add the cream of celery soup and butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for a few minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: jerry's beef stroganoff
directions: Pound meat to make thin and cut into finger length pieces, about 1/2-inch slices.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in frying pan, add onion and cook until onion is yellow.
Simmer slowly.
Add beef and cook quickly, about 5 minutes, turning pieces to brown all sides.
Set aside.
Slice mushrooms unless mushroom pieces are used and saute in remaining butter.
Season with salt and add dash of nutmeg and add to beef.
Add parsley and dill.
Mix bouillon and sour cream together.
Add to meat mixture.
Heat thoroughly and serve over rice, potato or noodles.
Fillet is only good when cooked quickly and served pinky-rare.

title: hungarian beef stew
directions: Put all meat, onion, potatoes, carrots, peas, garlic, parsley and green pepper in crock-pot.
Mix together broth, paprika, salt and tomatoes.
Pour over top.
Stir.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in casserole, alternating layers of potatoes and onion.
To make sauce, melt butter, mushroom soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potatoes with pecan topping
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and put in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, nuts, flour and melted oleo.
Sprinkle on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oreo cookie balls
directions: Crush Oreo cookies, then mix them with the cream cheese. Either form them into balls or use a cookie dough dispenser and place them onto wax. Place them in the refrigerator for 30 minutes or so.

title: crisco decorator icing
directions: Mix Crisco, salt, vanilla and about 1/3 of the sugar. Add milk and remaining sugar alternately.
Mix until smooth.
Beat with electric mixer for fluffy icing.
Can be used in decorator bags. Can be stored in refrigerator, covered, for weeks.

title: baked curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits well in colander until all juice has run off, 1 to 2 hours.
Prepare shallow casserole (8 x 12-inches or similar size) by greasing it with margarine.
Add fruit; cover with mixture of brown sugar and curry powder.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and dot with margarine.
Cover and bake 1 hour in oven at 300°.
Yield:
12 servings, about 2 quarts.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach in a pan until tender with onion; drain well. Add Velveeta cheese, sharp Cheddar cheese and sour cream and mix. Top with croutons (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: deviled steak
directions: Brown onions.
Brown steak separately.
Cover steak with dry ingredients which have been made thin enough with vinegar to pour on.
Then finish covering steak with enough water to finish filling skillet.
Allow to simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: raspberry almond tartlets
directions: Mix
all-purpose
flour and butter until crumbly.
Beat egg yolk,
almond
extract
and water.
With a fork, stir egg mixture lightly into flour mixture and mix until smooth.
Beat almond paste,
butter,
egg
white, powdered sugar and Kirsch cherry juice.
Pinch
off
3/4 inch balls of pastry dough and press
each into
ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin pan.
Fill each pastry
shell 2/3 full with almond mixture.
Heat preserves in small
pan
until bubbles.
Spoon
a little of preserves over each
tartlet
to glaze.
Cool
before removing from pans and serve.

title: no-cook fondant
directions: Basic Recipe:
In large bowl, stir together margarine, corn syrup, vanilla and salt until blended and smooth.
Add confectioners sugar all at once and mix in, first with spoon, then kneading with hands.

title: pigeon peas and rice
directions: Fry bacon; add onion
and
saute.
Add	pigeon peas and 1/2 can of water.
Bring to
a	boil;
add rice, dash of thyme and bay leaves.
Simmer for 15
to 20 minutes or until rice is soft.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Pour in remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Divide batter into 3 greased, floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Bake small pans about 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 3 large loaves or 6 miniature loaves.

title: wanda-ful cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a graham cracker crust.
Put the crust in a spring-form pan.
Make sure the crust goes at least halfway up the side of the pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and lemon juice.
Mix well but leave a little lumpy.
Bake 1/2 hour or until cake sets firm.
Remove from oven and turn oven up to 450°.

title: polish noodles and  cabbage
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Add cabbage and saute 5 minutes, or until tender, but still crisp.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and marshmallows in 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir well.
Continue to microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes until mixture boils.
Then microwave on 50% (Medium) and boil 4 minutes.
Grate or chop chocolate into small pieces and add to hot mixture.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Add pecans and pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let cool before cutting into squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: steak royale
directions: Roll steak in flour.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and brown in skillet.
Cut 8 to 10 strips of green pepper and lay over meat. Mix separately soup mix and water.
Add ketchup and Worcestershire.
Pour soup mixture over steak and pepper in a pressure cooker or crock-pot.
Cook in pressure cooker for 20 minutes.
Or cook in crock-pot all day.
Serve with rice, boiled potatoes or mashed potatoes and my Green Bean Recipe.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add beaten egg yolks, vanilla and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Line pudding dish with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Pour pudding over wafers and bananas.

title: date cheese balls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Have butter and cheese at room temperature and combine with dry ingredients.
Form dough around date halves.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields 2 cups.

title: marinated lettuce salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: chewies
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix together the brown sugar, flour, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into pan with butter (press).
Sprinkle with coconut (press down).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
(Nuts may be chopped or crushed.)

title: teriyaki meat marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over meat and marinate at room temperature for at least one hour, turning meat several times.
Great on the grill.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour pan. Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan. Mix all other ingredients for about 2 minutes and pour on nuts in pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: sausage souffl
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a large, sturdy ziptop bag. Add chicken, seal bag and turn to coat chicken. Refrigerate, turning bag occasionally, at least 2 hours or up to 12.

title: stir-fry pork, onions and apples
directions: Combine soy, catsup, vinegar and cornstarch in small bowl. Stir in brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Stir-fry pork in 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet until browned on all sides. Remove with slotted spoon.
Reserve.
Add oil to skillet.
Add onions and apples; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add pork.
Stir soy mixture and add to skillet.
Stir-fry until mixture thickens and boils. Serve with hot rice.

title: beef appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Place in a round pan.
Place whole pecans (salted and sauteed in butter) on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix as listed.
Batter will be thick.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Reserve 3 1/2 tablespoons drippings. Set bacon aside.
In large saucepan, pour drippings.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring often.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir together sour cream, flour and paprika.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of hot mix into sour cream mix; return to soup.
Cook and stir just until soup bubbles.
Top with crumbled bacon and serve.

title: green bean italian
directions: Place beans in lightly greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish. Sprinkle onion over beans; arrange tomatoes evenly over onion. Bake,
uncovered,
in
a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: ambers delight freeze
directions: Mix ingredients; freeze and cut to serve.

title: chicken-zucchini parmigiana
directions: In large skillet, saute garlic in oil until brown.
Discard garlic.

title: granola cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, granulated sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls; place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, but not hard, 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.
Yield: approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: arkansas shrimp
directions: Place cut chicken strips in a medium size bowl; add salt, monosodium glutamate and pepper.
In the meantime, mix the remaining ingredients except margarine.
Pour mixture over chicken pieces and let stand about 15 minutes.
Fry chicken strips in margarine until done.
Serve with sauce.

title: cherry-pineapple salad
directions: Combine pie filling, pineapple, nuts and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: salmon salad
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients well and add white vinegar a little at a time to blend ingredients and taste smooth.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: granny's egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix milk, sugar, vanilla and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into baked pie shell. Bake slow until done. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: hamburger and rice dinner
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, pepper and garlic.
Drain.
Add soup, tomatoes, water and mushrooms.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put on top of rice.

title: fudge cake aristocrat
directions: Place chocolate in mixing bowl.
Add water, stirring until chocolate melts.
Add bran and set aside to cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar into cooled mixture.
Add shortening and beat 2 minutes (200 strokes).
Add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch pans and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Ice with Fudge Frosting (follows).

title: hoppin john soup
directions: Brown sausage and chopped onion in 2-quart pan.
Add black-eyed peas and water and bring to a boil.
Stir in margarine, salt and pepper and cook on medium heat 15 minutes.
Stir in rice and cook 10 minutes.

title: swiss 'n bacon quiche
directions: Sprinkle
bacon (crumbled), onion and Swiss cheese over crust. Beat together evaporated
milk, eggs, salt and nutmeg. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350°
for
35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center	comes
out
clean.
Let
set
before serving.

title: apricot appeals
directions: Take a deep muffin tin.
In each ring, put 1 teaspoon melted butter.
Add 1 tablespoon of brown sugar to melt.
Place about 3 stewed dried apricots (depending on size of muffin tin) on the sugar in each ring.
Sift dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add liquids; mix until smooth.
Put batter in ring on top of apricots.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Turn upside-down as soon as taken from the oven.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix together spinach, 3/4 cup grated cheese, egg and seasonings in a medium bowl and set aside.
Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a layer of dry noodles on top of sauce.
Place half of the spinach mixture over noodles. Cover noodles with 2 cups of sauce, other half of spinach mixture and top with noodles.
Spoon remaining sauce over noodles.
Pour water around edges of pan.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove foil and cover with grated cheese.
Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add the milk and mix to a batter that will drop from a spoon.
Drop from a spoon into the boiling stew, being sure of enough juice and no possibility of boiling dry.
Cover undisturbed for 10 to 20 minutes, depending on the size of the dumpling.

title: my mama's doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Dough will be slightly stiff.
Refrigerate for several hours so that dough will be easier to handle.
Before rolling out, heat your oil to about 375°.
(I don't have an exact on this because Mama just always knew when it was hot enough by trying a donut hole.)

title: fried onion rings
directions: Cut
onions
into 1/4-inch slices; separate rings.
Dip into thin
batter
made	from milk, flour, melted shortening, salt, pepper and egg.
Fry in hot shortening or oil, enough to cover onions, until brown; drain.

title: lace cookies
directions: Melt butter. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on cookie sheets which have been covered with well greased foil. Leave plenty of room for them to spread out, approximately 6 to 8 cookies per sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes (until golden brown). Cool and peel from foil. You need 1 to 1 1/2 hours free to stand by the stove.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: For Gypsy Chicken Paprikas
first you steal a chicken.

title: naimo bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.
Mix 1 cup margarine, sugar, cocoa, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Cook in top of a double boiler until thickened like custard.
Add graham cracker crumbs and nuts.
Place in pan to cool.
Do not cook.
Just mix cream, 1/2 cup butter, confectioners sugar, milk and cornstarch.
Spread on top of first layer and let stand for 20 minutes.
Then melt baking chocolate with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Pour evenly on top of second mixture.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rice, in crock-pot.
Simmer all day.
Prepare rice and serve beef tips on a bed of rice.
If more of the gravy is desired, add additional soup.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 2 hours.
You can add bacon bits (optional).

title: cindy's corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops in a crust
directions: Place chops in shallow pan and add milk to cover.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours at room temperature.
Combine potato flakes with seasonings.
Drain chops, press into dry mixture, coating well on both sides.
Brush broiler rack with a little oil.
Place chops on rack in high position, sprinkle top with oil.
Turn.
Broil 15 to 18 minutes.
About 10 minutes before chops are done, brush 6 slices of pineapple with oil and sprinkle with a little sugar. Place on rack around the chops.
Broil about 4 minutes.
Turn. Broil until chops are ready.
Place a piece of pineapple on each chop and serve.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat.
Add green onion.
Cook over low heat until tender but do not brown.
Add tomato sauce, chili peppers, Worcestershire and cheese.
Cook, stirring occasionally until all cheese is melted.
Stir in garlic powder.
Serve in a chafing dish over low heat.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 1 quart.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini, nuts and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon which have been sifted together.
Mix until well blended. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Cut and dry lettuce.
Parboil peas (return to package and place in freezer to cool).
Chop onion and celery.

Line 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish with lettuce and layer celery, onion and peas. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar or Sweet 'N Low over this mixture. Spread mayonnaise, sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese. Return to refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with 6 strips of crisp crumbled bacon.

title: coconut pound cake(start in cold oven)
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Gradually add eggs, one at a time, beating for 2 minutes after each.
Add flour alternating with milk, blending in flour and coconut.
Add flavorings.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix and put in freezer until partly frozen (at least 1/2 hour).
Then swirl cherry pie filling all through it and freeze.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat the egg whites until fluffy. Combine the yolks.
Add and beat together the sugar, buttermilk, soda, baking powder, salt, flour and grease.
Fold in egg whites.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Add all the ingredients in a large bowl and add salad dressing.
Mix well.
Add or omit any vegetables you personally do not like.

title: mimi's special sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add margarine, beating well. Add flavoring and flour slowly.
Chill dough.
Roll and cut.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes millions, or about 10 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a large frying pan in 1 to 2 teaspoons oil.
Add chicken, tomatoes, chili powder, cumin and water.
Heat to boiling (may need more liquid).
Dip tortillas in hot vegetable oil, not smoking, but enough to sizzle.
To save calories, dip in hot broth.
Scoop 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture into each tortilla.
Roll and place in a shallow baking dish.
Top with sour cream and Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serve with salad and fried rice.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl; let set.

title: baked rice
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fish batter
directions: Dip fish in batter; fry in very hot grease until brown.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Put cereal in a large bowl.
In 1 quart microwave safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter, and margarine.
Microwave on high 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth stirring after 1 minute. stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over cereal.
Stir until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal into brown paper bag with powdered sugar and shake to coat cereal.
Do this step with small amounts several times.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: kraut salad
directions: When cool, pour over kraut mixture.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp creole(total cooking time:  14 to 15 minutes)
directions: In 2-quart microproof casserole, combine green onions, celery, green pepper, butter and garlic.
Cook, covered, on High (Maximum power) 3 minutes or until green onions are transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, on 80 (Reheat) 5 minutes. Stir.
Cook, covered, on 80 (Reheat) 6 to 7 minutes or until hot. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving over hot cooked rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: moms old-fashioned boiled custard
directions: Make in 2 batches. Place 1/2 gal. milk on stove in heavy pot. Bring almost to boil; do not allow to boil. Add vanilla to taste, about 1 tsp. Separate eggs. Beat egg yolks and whites separately. Add 3/4 cup sugar to each batch. Then add egg yolks.

title: fajitas stir-fry
directions: Cut beef or chicken with the grain into 1-inch wide strips, then cut each strip across the grain into 1/8-inch thick slices. Set aside.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling on bottom of cake pan.
Top with dry cake mix.
Pour melted butter on top.
Add drained pineapple.
Top with coconut.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Combine ingredients in glass jar; cover for 24 hours.

title: hamburg soup
directions: In a large heavy pan, brown hamburg, stirring slightly to break up pieces.
Drain off excess fat.
Add all other ingredients except barley.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered for 45 minutes.
Add barley and simmer for another 15 minutes.
Taste and adjust seasonings, if needed.
Remove the bay leaf and serve.

title: fresh strawberry no crust pie
directions: Using a 10-inch pie dish, distribute 2 cups of strawberries evenly in pie dish.

title: spoon tacos
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
On a plate, place a handful of tortilla chips. Spoon meat mixture on top of chips.
Follow with lettuce, cheese, tomato and sour cream.
Serves 4.
Prep time:
15 minutes.
Great for camping!

title: chocolate nut cake
directions: Cream butter and egg yolks; add sugar and cream until fluffy. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and fold in whipped egg whites.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana dessert
directions: Beat for 15 minutes, no
less.
Then spread over crumbs. Spread 1 layer of bananas over
filling.
Whip 1 pint cream. Sweeten.
Spread over and cover all bananas.
Put
nuts
and maraschino
cherries
over cream.
Chill 6 hours.

title: reunion beans
directions: Clean and soak beans approximately 2 hours.
Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a 13 gal. iron pot. Spice with salt, pepper & seasoning to taste.
Cook for 2 1/2 - 3 hours.
By the time you drink 6-12 beers and B.S. with relatives, the beans are ready to serve with love.
The way this family eats, if you expect to get any beans, be in line early!
Pot usually lasts 10-15 minutes.
You will probably have enough "NATURAL" gas the next day to cook 4 or 5 pots of beans.

title: white icing
directions: Beat the egg white and shortening well.
Add powdered sugar and milk or cream so icing will spread well.
Beat at least 4 minutes.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a large Dutch oven. Cover with water 2-inches above beans; let soak overnight.
Drain beans. Combine beans, 5 cups water, celery, onion, carrots, parsley and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf!

title: ten can soup
directions: Saute ground beef and onion; drain grease.
Add cans of vegetables and cook for about 30 minutes.
Use a big Dutch oven. This makes a bunch.
It also freezes well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and combine with other ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° or until cheese is melted well.

title: beef stew
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Line with hamburg and onions, salt and pepper.
Fill dish with sliced raw potatoes and cover with a can of undrained peas.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in large bowl; blend well. Bring to boil butter, water and cocoa; mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to batter.
Pour in greased and floured sheet pan or 2 round pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: reuben brunch casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Arrange bread cubes on bottom.
Coarsely shred corned beef.
Layer meat over the bread.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and pepper. Pour over the beef mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake casserole covered for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more or until puffed and bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and spread into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
(May be refrigerated at this point.)
When ready to bake, sprinkle with topping made of 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup slivered almonds.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes and coat thoroughly.
Bake 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Stir occasionally so potatoes will be cooked evenly.
Garnish, if desired, with parsley.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Mix together last 6 ingredients.
Melt margarine in a pan. Pour in mixture.
Add fruit.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup sugar and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix milk, soups and mushrooms.
In saucepan, melt margarine; add 1 cup of hot water.
Add this to the stuffing.
Sprinkle topping over chicken and soups.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and bubbling.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix evaporated milk and powdered sugar with mixer.
Mix the sour cream and Cool Whip, then combine with evaporated milk-powdered sugar mix.
Tear the angel food cake into bite size pieces; combine with above mixture.
If frozen, thaw the strawberries.
If they have excessive juice, drain some off. Combine the strawberries with the glaze.
Layer the two mixtures in a clear glass bowl.
Better if it sits overnight.
Needs to be refrigerated.

title: polenta gnocchi with gorgonzola
directions: In a large saucepan, slowly pour water into the cornmeal, stirring constantly, until free of lumps. Stir in rest of water and salt. Cook on medium-low heat for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently, until thick and smooth. Be especially vigilant during last 10 minutes to prevent scorching. When polenta is done, spoon will stand up in the middle and mass will cling together and pull away from the sides. Remove from heat and turn onto countertop, baking sheet or cutting board that has been wet down with cold water to prevent sticking. Smooth out polenta with spatula. Let cool 30 minutes. Brush the bottom and sides of baking dish with some of the melted butter. Brush the rest of the butter on top of the polenta. Cut the polenta into small rounds. Take all of the little 4-sided pieces of the polenta from between the rounds and place them in a baking dish. On top of these, make an overlapping row of rounds leaning up against the sides of the dish (like tile roof tops). Crumble Gorgonzola over the top and bake in a 450° oven for 20 minutes. Can be covered and refrigerated until baking time.

title: frito pie(great for camping)
directions: In medium baking dish layer Fritos.
Cover with chili and grated cheese.
Heat until warm through and serve with chopped onions.
If camping, just heat beans and serve over Fritos.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 to 7 minutes; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients except cheese.
Layer broccoli, soup mixture and broccoli, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add topping.

title: mom's chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Chop onion; cook in with meat.
Add mix, water, beans and tomatoes.
Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef and onions together.
Drain.
Mix taco seasoning in beef.
Place crescent rolls in large pie pan.
Then layer ground beef mixture, sour cream, shredded cheese and nacho chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add soup.
Combine flour, soda, powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Combine with listed ingredients.
Add nuts and cherries, saving some for the top of the cake.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: bacon-fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture. Fry bacon partially in 10-inch skillet.
Cook chicken and bacon over medium heat until chicken is brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer, turning chicken once or twice, until thickest pieces are done, 20 to 30 minutes.
(If skillet cannot be covered tightly, add 1 to 2 tablespoons water.)
Uncover and cook 10 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla
directions: Split vanilla beans open lengthwise.
Add to bottle of rum. Let sit 1 year.
Turn bottle upside down occasionally to mix.

title: teriyaki steak skewers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand for about 30 minutes. Cut steak into strips about 1/4-inch thick by 1-inch wide.
Add to sauce. Stir to coat. Let stand 2 hours!!

title: fluffy biscuit muffins
directions: In a bowl cut flour and mayonnaise together until mixture resembles coarse crumbs
Add milk; stir until mixed.
spoon into four greased muffin cups.
Bake at 425 degrees for 14 - 16 minutes or until light brown.
Yield 4 biscuits.

title: mints
directions: Mix the ingredients together with hands.
Take a small amount and roll into long strips, about 3/4-inch in diameter on a powdered surface.
Slice with butter knife or use a cookie press. Let dry overnight.

title: pork ribs with kraut
directions: Cook ribs in 3 cups of water in large saucepan for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook
for 15 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings, about 700 calories each.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix together tomato soup, sugar, mustard and garlic salt.
Add vinegar and oil.
Mix well.
Let stand 24 hours before using. (Always refrigerate.)
Shake well before using.

title: chocolate chip cookie pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Spread cookie dough onto pan until dough touches sides of pan.
Bake at 350° in oven until cookie dough is done.
Let cool and decorate as to the occasion!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until onion is done.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Mix oil slowly with other ingredients.
Add poppy seed last. Refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in flour that's been seasoned with salt and pepper in cooking oil.
Wash kraut in water 2 times and add to meat, then add soup and simmer 30 to 40 minutes on stovetop or in oven.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix in.
Bake in loaf or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
For holidays, add 1 cup of candied fruit.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until just tender.
Slice thin.
Fry bacon slowly in skillet.
Drain on paper.
Saute onion and celery in bacon fat until brown.
Add flour, sugar, salt, pepper, mustard and caraway seed.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly. Stir in water and vinegar.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add potatoes and crumbled bacon.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Can be served hot, room temperature or cold.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare browned beef with taco seasoning following packet directions.
In large bowl combine vegies as they are prepared. Mix vegies into slightly cooled, seasoned beef.
Stir in dressing. Toss in tortilla chips.

title: iris' corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix together with rest of the ingredients.

title: continental zucchini
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Saute zucchini and garlic for 3 to 4 minutes. Add pimientos, corn, salt, if desired and lemon-pepper. Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes or until zucchini is tender. Sprinkle with cheese and heat until cheese is melted. Yield: 6 servings.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Add oil; mix well.
Add oats, cornflakes and nuts, stirring well.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Form into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Allow to cool on cookie sheets before removing.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add 2 cups flour with baking powder.
Mix in flavoring.
Coat nuts and fruit with 2 cups flour.
Add to cream mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cover and leave overnight.
Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken breasts until size doubles. Rub Parmesan cheese into each side. Dip chicken in egg whites and press bread crumbs on both sides. Saut 3 to 5 minutes per side in skillet sprayed with nonstick spray. Yield: 4 servings.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Combine zucchini, water, onion, salt, parsley and 1 bouillon cube.
Cook until zucchini is tender and small amount of water is left.
Mash; put through sieve or puree with blender.
In saucepan, melt butter; add flour, pepper and last bouillon cube. Blend well.
Add milk and simmer until thickened.
Stir in zucchini mixture, mixing well.
(If soup is too thick, add milk.)

title: raspberry vinegar
directions: Place raspberries in clean 16-ounce (1 pint) jar; add vinegar. Microwave on High approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Vinegar should reach 140° to 150°.

title: onion cheese muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Fill 16 greased medium muffin cups 2/3 full, bake about 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Simmer clams in own juice with lemon juice until 1/2 volume. Saut all ingredients, but breadcrumbs and cheese, in butter. Add clams and breadcrumbs to mixture. Put in crock or any oven-safe dish. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with crackers and Tabasco.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together.
Let freeze in milk cartons.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Chop up the frozen mixture.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: In skillet in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove and set aside.
Spoon off fat.
In skillet add rest of ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet. Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until chicken is not longer pink and broccoli is tender-crisp, stirring often.
Garnish with tomato wedges and fresh thyme.
Cook 25 minutes.

title: layered dip
directions: Layer bean dip and guacamole.
Mix taco seasoning mix and sour cream and layer.
Layer green chilies, black olives, Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheese.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed. Serve with tortilla chips, Fritos, spoons or fingers.

title: avocado dip
directions: Gradually add avocado to cream cheese and blend until smooth. Add lemon juice, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.

title: ribs
directions: Combine tomato sauce, steak sauce, sorghum, ketchup, lemon juice, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce in a medium saucepan.
Stir over low heat until thoroughly heated, about 10 minutes.
Place ribs on grill over medium heat.
Baste with sauce.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes, basting and turning ribs every 10 to 15 minutes.
The ribs are done when the internal temperature reaches 180°, when the ribs are flexible and fork tender and when the ends of the bones extend about 1/2-inch beyond the meat.
Ribs may also be basted and baked in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: sherry almond custard
directions: Soften gelatin in water; add hot milk and mix well.
Beat eggs until thick and add sugar.
Mix well.
Stir milk into egg mixture; add sherry and salt.
Chill until thick.
Fold in whipping cream and almonds.
Pour into cups and top with vanilla wafers, crushed. Chill or freeze.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: barbecue cornbread
directions: Mix well; bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: orange biscuits
directions: A tube pan or Bundt pan is needed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a casserole dish.
Pour over the bread crumbs; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together and put into dish.
Add bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa to a rolling boil. Cook 1/2 minute.
Remove from fire; add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Stir 2 or 3 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries (thawed), sliced bananas and drained pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Freeze until solid.

title: feather sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add cold water. Beat until very thick.
Gradually beat in sugar, then add vanilla and lemon flavor.
Sift flour with salt.
Fold into yolk mixture, a little at a time.

title: microwave asparagus-ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Cut in half crosswise.
Melt butter in pan.
Stir in flour and cook over low heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in milk and cook.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thickened. Add garlic, thyme and pepper.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons sauce in bottom of square 2-quart casserole dish.
Place layer of noodles over sauce, then layer 1/2 of the ham, 1/2 can asparagus, 1/2 cup of the sauce and 1/3 cup of mixed cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles and last of sauce and cheese.
Cook on High power for 9 to 10 minutes, turning it twice.

title: tomato salad
directions: Wash and peel tomatoes.
Cut into small trenches (do not drain juice).
Wash and cut green onions (small pieces).
Cut and squeeze lime (1/2 teaspoon).
Put tomato trenches into medium size bowl.
Add green onions, vegetable oil, lime juice and a pinch of salt.
Stir a couple of times.
Refrigerate 30 minutes to one hour.

title: taco noodle bake
directions: Brown onion in beef.
Stir in sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In a bowl combine cheese, sour cream and bouillon. Add cooked noodles.
Blend all together.
Put in casserole dish. Place Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour and saute chicken 3 to 4 minutes each side in oil in skillet until golden brown.
Mix tomatoes, salsa, onion and spices together and pour over chicken and cover and simmer 20 minutes until chicken is tender.
Spoon on top of rice; top with sauce.
Garnish with sour cream and avocado or guacamole.

title: snowy strawberry squares
directions: Prepare dessert mix according to package, except use all milk in place of water.
Gently stir in mashed berries, pineapple, nuts and mayonnaise.
Whip cream; fold into mixture.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: john's favorite apple pie
directions: Heat juice with dissolved cornstarch in it.
Add margarine and cinnamon.
If you overheat, it will be too thick. Add apples. Stir carefully, just to coat.
Pour into uncooked pie crust.
Cover with the other pie crust.
Make 4 small slits in top crust.
Put margarine on top and sprinkle top with more cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes at 300° or until golden brown.
Place on baking sheet.
It will bubble over a little. Great for diabetics or dieters (1 starch, 1 fruit, 1 fat).

title: pickled okra and hot peppers
directions: Use small okra pods.
Cut off ends but don't cut into okra. Dip into boiling water for a few seconds, until color changes. Drain at once.
Pack in hot jars; add 3 or 4 peppers to your taste.
Fill jars with white boiling vinegar.
Seal.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; boil slowly for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain.
Melt oleo; saute bell pepper and onion until tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper and pimento; blend.
Add milk and cook until sauce begins to thicken.
