Add cheeses and cook on low heat until cheeses are melted and blended.
Place potatoes in a casserole dish; pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: western mac
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Brown meat, celery, green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel crunch apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place crust in 9-inch pie plate.
Turn under edge and flute.
Melt caramels with water in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Spoon apples into crust; top with caramel sauce.
Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in walnuts.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tomato fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter.
Heat butter in a skillet over moderate heat and drop in mixture by spoonfuls.
Fry to a delicate brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spanokopetes
directions: Thaw frozen spinach 2 hours at room temperature.
Saute green onions in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Add spinach and simmer until almost all the liquid evaporates.
Crumble Feta cheese into large bowl.
Add cottage cheese, eggs, parsley and dill weed.
Mix well.
Add spinach mixture and mix until thoroughly blended.
Layer 1/2 of phyllo pastry in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, brushing each sheet of pastry with melted butter.
Spread cheese mixture evenly over top of phyllo.
Repeat layering with remaining phyllo, brushing each sheet with butter.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 25 minutes.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate nut bark
directions: Place chocolate in 1-quart casserole.
Place in microwave. Cook 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Stir well.
Place a piece of wax paper on cookie sheet.
Spread mixture in a thin layer on wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Break into pieces. Makes 3/4 pound.

title: garlic pasta sauce
directions: Heat oil and brown garlic until light brown.
Add onion and bell
pepper;
cook
a
little and add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Simmer
for
minutes.
Add
water;
bring to boil. Reduce heat;
simmer
for 20 minutes.
Cook thin spaghetti or angel
hair pasta; drain.
Pour sauce over pasta; blend well. Sprinkle with grated Italian cheese.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice.
Add jello and mix well.
Cool and add 2 cups buttermilk.
When partly jelled, add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 12-inch container and refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: potato scramble
directions: Cook onion and carrot in the water 5 minutes.
Add potatoes; steam 15 minutes, adding a little more water if necessary.
Add the mushrooms and soy sauce; cook 10 minutes.
Good for any meal!

title: hefty cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage and cut up; set aside.
Fry sausage in heavy pot or large skillet.
Add cabbage and 1 glass water.
Stir and cook until cabbage is almost done; add potatoes.
Cook until potatoes tender (salt and pepper to taste when you add the cabbage to sausage).
Stir often, scraping drippings from bottom of pot. This makes cabbage and potatoes brown.
Add a little water at a time as needed to loosen crust from bottom of pot.

title: orange fluff
directions: Drain pineapple. Combine cottage cheese, cool whip and jello well. Add in pineapple and pecans. Break orange pieces in half and gently stir into mixture. Keep refrigerated.

title: sausage apple balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 4 dozen balls.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Mix together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture. Combine cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar in small bowl.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients lightly.
Add bananas and blend.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and beat slowly. Chill before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Can be kept in refrigerator for a week or 10 days before baking.

title: batter for fish, chicken, etc.
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add just enough beer to make batter adhere to meat.
Cook meat in deep fat at 400° until the batter is brown and crisp.
This is enough batter for 3 pounds of fish.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain.
Add sour cream and onion soup mix.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with a mixture of bread crumbs, margarine and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl beat cheese fluffy.
Beat
in
milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in
lemon juice and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill
hours.
Before serving, drizzle syrup over top of pie
for
garnish.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: red satin punch
directions: Pour 1/2 the 7-Up in ice cube trays and freeze.
Place 7-Up cubes in punch bowl.
Pour remaining 7-Up, apple juice and cranberry juice cocktail over top.
Stir until blended.
Serve in punch cups.
Yields 24 cups.

title: crabmeat bake
directions: Clean crabmeat, pick out shell.
Mix all ingredients except buttered crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
This can be prepared a day ahead and reheated.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Soften 1 pint sherbet.
In punch bowl, combine softened sherbet, lemon, orange juice, to sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Add cranberry juice. Refrigerate up to 5 hours.
Before serving punch, add ginger ale, mixing well. Scoop remaining sherbet into balls to float in punch.
Makes 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Chop peaches with juice. Spread into a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle cake mix over peaches. Melt oleo and drizzle over top. Sprinkle coconut and nuts over all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: About 20 minutes before serving in large kettle (or pot) over medium heat, heat all ingredients except orange juice.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add orange juice.
Drain off spices if you like. Serve hot.
Makes 36 servings, 3/4 cup each.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken; skin, debone and finely chop.
Add eggs, celery, onion, relish and pecans.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add mayonnaise.
Yields enough to make a salad or sandwich spread. Can be doubled very well.

title: molded fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice, eggs, sugar and flour.
Cook over low heat until thick (about 5 minutes).
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool before adding orange sections, bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: maklooba(chicken turnover)
directions: Remove green cone from eggplant, then slice eggplant lengthwise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place eggplant slices in a colander. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon salt on them.
Set aside for one hour so that the juice drains from the eggplant.

title: pumpkin bread roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes at high speed.
Beat in sugar.
Fold in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold both mixtures together. Put in greased jelly roll pan and top with ground nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes at 300°.
Place in dish towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up and allow to cool.

title: chunky chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a small bowl. Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter in large mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Press down slightly to flatten into 2-inch circles. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes or until edges are set, but centers are still soft. Let stand for 4 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool completely. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Beat well the eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add milk and whip again.
Break bread into pieces and add to mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: * Goya brand is one of the best.

title: b.b.q. oysters-cajun style
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and
coat oysters.
Deep fry in hot oil 4-5 minutes.

title: brownies cockaigne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate in a double boiler and cool this mixture.
Beat eggs and salt until light in color and foamy in texture.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually and continue beating until well creamed.
With a few swift strokes (manually), combine cooled chocolate mixture into eggs and sugar. Before the mixture becomes uniformly colored, fold in flour (again manually).
Before flour is uniformly colored, gently stir in pecans.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes. Cut when cool.
Wrap individually in foil; these keep well for 3 to 4 days.
Good way to serve brownies is to garnish with whipped cream.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Measure sifted flour, then sift again with dry ingredients into bowl.
Measure shortening.
With pastry blender, cut it into dry ingredients quickly and lightly until mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Scoop a deep well in flour mixture and add milk all at once.
Stir gently with fork until flour is dampened.
Stir vigorously, just until dough follows fork around bowl.

title: creamy lemon pudding cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix, wafer crumbs, sugar and butter; press firmly into bottom of 9 inch spring form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Pat out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips in microwave; spread on top.

title: banana loaf
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs together.
Mix in 3 large bananas.
Add flour, soda, nuts and vanilla.
Put in 2 small bread loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then bake at 325° for another 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except French fried onions, in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover; sprinkle with onions and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 12 cup Bundt pan. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and set aside.
Beat butter in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugars and continue beating until very light.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine milk and flavorings.
Add to batter alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: salsa
directions: Add ingredients and salt to taste.
Use as a dip for chips.

title: easy quick quiche
directions: Mix egg, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Crumble bacon (or sausage) on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cheese and onion.
Pour liquid over meat and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown and a toothpick comes out clean.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk; mix until blended. Stir in crab meat, onion and cheese.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set, 40 or 45 minutes.
Recipe from friend.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix crackers, margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar together; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chocolate chips over top.
Melt in oven for a few minutes.
Spread chips when melted, then cover and chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla. Add rest of ingredients.
Make into balls; press down with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: old time gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice hot dish
directions: Mix together and bake 1 1/2 hours or longer at 350°.
Stir often.

title: moma's beef stew
directions: Roll meat in mix of flour, salt, and pepper until coated and brown in vegetable oil.
In regular size pressure cooker, put browned meat (I use my rack so it doesn't scorch).
Add potatoes, carrots, and onions.
Then, add salt and pepper.
Pour 1 c. water over vegetables.
Cook at 15 lb. pressure for 30 minutes.
Moma always served this with corn bread and cole slaw.

title: red dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with a mixer for 10 minutes. Just like the kind at the pizza shop.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and put into pan with cold water, 1/2 cup salt and sliced onions.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, and flour. Beat milk and egg yolks. Stir all together. Microwave 4 minutes. Stir. Cook again 3 - 4 minutes. Add margarine and vanilla. Cook and then pour over into baked crust.

title: "simply easiest" broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Add all remaining ingredients, except crackers.
Place in baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set.

title: beef with sour cream
directions: Remove bone and fat from steak; cut into thin, narrow strips. Dredge in flour.
Brown meat quickly in hot skillet on all sides. Add onions, broth, thyme and liquid from mushrooms.
Cover; simmer for about 45 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms and peas.
Cover and cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat but do not boil.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with pimiento, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry-pear chutney
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, bring cranberries, pears, onion, sugar, vinegar, lemon zest, ginger, allspice, salt and pepper to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes or until cranberries burst.
Let cool.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter pan; put in pie filling. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Spread dry cake mix over filling.
Take margarine and cut in pats; place 1 1/2 to 2 inches apart (make sure margarine is in corners and along sides).
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: italian broccoli casserole
directions: Combine eggs, Cheddar cheese soup and oregano.
Stir in drained tomatoes and cooked broccoli.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Put in greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake is baking, sift 2 cups confectioners sugar and mix with the juice of two large lemons.
While cake is hot, poke all over with fork and drizzle lemon and sugar mix all over it.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Bring this mixture to a boil and boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add last three ingredients.
Beat until it starts to thicken. Turn into well buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake, covered, 2 hours at 325°.
Uncover during last 1/2 hour.

title: berry cheesecake bars
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients until crumbly. Set aside 1/2 cups. Press rest into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly brown. Beat cream cheese to soften. Add sweetened condensed milk. Stir in ReaLemon juice. Spread on crust. Combine cranberry and cornstarch. Add remaining 1 tablespoon sugar. Spoon over cheese layer. Top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and cut into bars.

title: 9th street restaurant tea
directions: In a gallon jar mix
the
dry
ingredients,
then add a little hot water to dissolve it.
Add
the
cups
of juice. Then finish filling the jar with cold water.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: squash-chicken casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain. Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix. Add mushroom soup, onion and chicken to drained squash, then add 1/2 stuffing mix. Pour into casserole dish. Top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: baked corn supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given, mixing well; do not beat.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: shirl's yummy dessert
directions: Mix together pie filling, pineapple and sweetened condensed milk. Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together (except bread) in pan, using low heat to melt cheese, stirring constantly. Spread on bread.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.
To make squares, put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple goodie
directions: Mix white sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add thinly sliced apples and toss until apples are thoroughly covered.
Place this in buttered baking dish.
Mix oatmeal and brown sugar, melt margarine and add this to mixture and mix.
Spread evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown or apples are tender.

title: spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add garlic salt, oregano, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Stir well.
Simmer for an hour.
Boil spaghetti noodles to taste; strain.
Eat, eat and eat.

title: hot garlic bread
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Cut bread into diagonal slices (1 inch thick).
Rub each slice with cut garlic.
Brush sides with olive oil and put on baking sheet.
Toast in oven until crispy.
Turn one time.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat yolks and add grated cheese, flour, milk, salt and pepper (will be stiff).
Fold in whites. Pour into well-buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cube cream cheese and dot over top of cheese mixture; poke in (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May add chopped chilies, shrimp, ham or chicken into egg yolk mixture.
If desired, serve with warmed green chili salsa (mild).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: canada war cake
directions: Boil all ingredients for 5 minutes after they begin to bubble. When cold, add 3 cups flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder and 1 scant teaspoon soda (dissolved in 1 tablespoon hot water).
Bake into loaves in a slow oven for 45 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
You may add nutmeats also if you like.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven or large kettle; add water to cover (about 8 cups). Add celery, carrot, onion, parsley, bay leaf, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Cover; bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is tender, about 2 hours for stewing chicken or about 1 hour for broiler fryers.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix and shape in walnut size balls.

title: potato soup with glaze
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender. Flavor with onion, parsley and salt. Add glaze to boiling water by teaspoonful. Boil about 5 minutes. Drain off water. Add enough milk to cover potatoes and glaze, 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper, to taste. Serve while hot.

title: seven course dinner
directions: Brown the beef lightly.
Put half in bottom of casserole.
On top of this put one layer sliced potatoes, one layer sliced celery, one layer sliced onion, one layer sliced carrots, the raw rice, one layer green pepper rings and 1 small can mushrooms.
Add the rest of the ground beef.
Mix the tomato soup with the water; pour over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: busy day chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with rice.
Arrange chicken pieces on rice.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with onion soup over all.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour boiling water into pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: pot pie(square dumplings)
directions: Combine ingredients; roll out and cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch squares.
Drop in boiling chicken or beef broth.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: savory sauce for fish or chicken
directions: Saute garlic and butter. Blend in flour and then remaining ingredients.
Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly. Cool.
Baste fish or chicken often.
Sprinkle meat with paprika. Yields 2 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° in an 11 x 13 pan or two 8-inch rounds that have been greased and floured. Bake for about 45 minutes or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean. When cooled ice with cream cheese icing.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil the sugar, butter and evaporated milk together for about 7 minutes (after first bubbles come or until a soft ball stage, 235° to 240°, is reached).
Put chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts in a large bowl.
Pour syrup over mixture and stir until chocolate is dissolved.
Beat until cool and creamy.
Drop on waxed paper or pour into greased pan; cool and cut into pieces. Yield:
5 pounds candy.

title: zucchini and mushrooms
directions: In large skillet, cook zucchini, mushrooms and onion in margarine until tender-crisp.
Add remaining ingredients; heat through.

title: country-style rib sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients into bowl; stir well.
Put 6 pounds of country-style ribs into pan.
Pour mixture over ribs.
Marinade overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put ribs on grill. Baste until done.

title: chocolate coconut squares
directions: Cook the corn syrup, water and sugar together in a small saucepan over medium heat to the soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat; add coconut and vanilla.
Melt baking pieces in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Pour over coconut, spread with spatula and sprinkle with nuts. Cool. Cut into squares.
Yields three dozen squares.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat corn syrup, chocolate and butter to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large bowl; toss quickly until completely covered with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press in pan with buttered spoon.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut in squares.

title: acini de pepe salad (frogs eye)
directions: Cook soup macaroni according to directions.
Drain all fruit, reserving juice from fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Measure 2 1/2 cups juice; combine with sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Cook until thick.
Pour over soup macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
Drain fruits again and add to soup macaroni mixture along with whipped topping and marshmallows.
Chill.
Makes large salad and freezes well.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well; form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Let set overnight.

title: spicy italian beans
directions: Brown ground chuck with salt, add Italian seasoning and pizza topping.
Add pasta sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix beans and pour into large baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch strips.
Salt and pepper to taste. Brown in a small amount of oil with onion.
Add 1 cup water and bouillon cubes.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour over low heat. Mix 1 cup water and cornstarch; add to meat.
Add celery and green pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce to taste.
At the last minute, add chopped tomatoes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heuvos con chorizo
directions: In a small amount of oil fry up diced pepper and chorizo. When sausage appears to be done, put in eggs and then scramble. This makes great tacos (corn or flour tortillas).
You can also eliminate the jalapeno pepper if you don't like spicy food.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Pour about 2 tablespoons oil in bottom of Dutch oven or skillet; add onions and saute.
Then add about 2 tablespoons flour to thicken sauce. Add tomatoes, Ro-Tel, Worcestershire, chili powder and catsup if desired. Let simmer; pour over spaghetti.
Mix well and then enjoy (I hope).
It's even better after it sets a while.

title: christmas fruitcake muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, stir together the egg, milk and butter, then stir them into the dry ingredients to make a lumpy batter.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.
Spoon the batter into greased muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake until well risen, golden and a thin wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: candied fruit cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour. Blend in pecans, fruit and cherries.
Form into a roll. Wrap with wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice very thin and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 6 to 8 minutes. This dough may be frozen.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Brown ground beef and season with salt and pepper.
Chop onion and green pepper; saute and add to beef.
Add pizza sauce.
Mix the mixture with cooked macaroni.
Put in casserole and top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and sliced pepperoni.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Cover for first 30 minutes.

title: cheese sandwich
directions: Put the butter down in the pan.
Put bread on it.
Then you put any kind of cheese on it.
Put bread on it.
Then you put butter on it.
Cook it on the stove.
Put stove on 2.
Cook 9 or 6 minutes.
Flip it over if brown; let the other side cook until brown.
Then do whatever you want to with it.

title: pink lozenger cake
directions: Dissolve lozengers in the 1 cup of milk overnight.
Mix shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Pour into greased 2 or 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: carrot pineapple bread
directions: Mix together the flour, soda, salt and sugar. Stir in oil, eggs, carrots and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 small pans, or 2 regular pans, bake 1 hour.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix Hidden Valley Ranch with mayonnaise and milk.
Add cream cheese.
Beat well with mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese and blend. Cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Shape into a ball and roll in toasted almonds.

title: low-sodium crock-pot meatballs
directions: *To serve over spaghetti, add 2 more cups of sauce.

title: fruit-melon salad
directions: Cut watermelon in half and scoop the edible portion and reserve for filling.
Cut a scallop edge around the rind.
Mix all of the fruits and melons except the
cherries and fill the rind. If you like, you may
garnish
sprinkling
the
coconut over the fruits and spacing the cherries on top.

title: tropical fruit smoothie
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients, except ice.
Blend well. Gradually add ice; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately; refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 5 cups.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole and bake covered for 5 hours at 250°, stirring occasionally.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with pepper and onion.
Drain liquid from beans.
Combine ketchup, sauces and mustard.
Drain meat and blend with beans and sauce.
Pour into large dish and let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana whip
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water in a blender.
Blend until dissolved, about 30 seconds.
Add milk and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir in blender until partially melted.
Add banana (sliced); blend until smooth.
Makes 2 3/4 cups or 5 servings; 45 calories per serving.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Place sliced bananas and wafers alternately in dish or pan. Simmer sugar and water about 10 minutes.
Separate egg yolks and whites.
Beat cream and egg yolks together.
Pour the boiling water and sugar over them.
Pour this over the wafers and bananas. Add 2 tablespoons of sugar for each egg white.
Beat until stiff. Place the meringue over the pudding and brown in a moderate oven. Cool and serve.

title: pumpkin spice bars
directions: I often make without raisins or nuts, depending on what you like.

title: crock-pot cabbage rolls
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, milk, onion, salt and pepper; mix well, then add rice and mix well.
Make sauce of tomato sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce; mix well in separate bowl.
Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water about 3 minutes or until limp; drain.
Place 1/4 cup meat mixture in center of each leaf; fold in sides and roll ends over meat.
Place in crock-pot; pour sauce over rolls.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours.

title: grandma's nut thin cookies
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add the well beaten eggs.
Sift in flour and salt.
Add finely chopped walnuts.
Add vanilla.
Mix until smooth and light.
Drop by 1/2 rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Place one walnut piece in center of each cookie and press down lightly.
Bake at
375° for 10 minutes or until light golden brown on edges.

title: strawberry and jello salad
directions: Mix well together and refrigerate.

title: pepper spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl, mixing thoroughly.
Mix until smooth.
Put in container.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Spread on crackers.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Two days ahead, prepare sourdough starter.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Place the carrots in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan and add the marmalade, orange juice and horseradish.
Cook, stirring frequently, over medium heat until all liquid has evaporated and the carrots are glazed.
Serves 2.

title: cole slaw
directions: Dissolve salt and sugar in vinegar; then mix it into the cut slaw.
Serve.
Keeps for months in the icebox.

title: german pancakes
directions: Whip eggs in blender or with mixer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and blend together for another 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide and pour into 2 well-greased pie plates.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; reduce heat to 350° for 10 minutes more. Butter; sprinkle with powdered sugar and squeeze lemon juice over all.

title: nanny's apple crunch
directions: Slice apples and layer in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in cup of water.
In large bowl mix cake mix, butter, cinnamon and pecans until small chunks form.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and dice artichokes.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with Wheat Thins crackers.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and vegetables together.
Add lime jello to mixture.
Use salad mold; chill until firm.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup and water.
Pour into casserole dish. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Prepare Stove Top according to package directions.
Spoon over top of chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat the oil and saute all veggies except kidney and garbanzo beans and tomatoes.
Add the spices and saute 3 minutes.
Add the beans, tomatoes and vinegar.
Use liquid from canned beans. Simmer for 45 minutes, or until all veggies are tender.
Yields 10 portions.

title: snack crackers
directions: Combine oil, dill and salad dressing mix.
Place crackers in a large bowl.
Pour dressing mixture over and toss gently. Allow to stand at least 1 hour before serving.
Yields 12 cups.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 1/2 of batter in 9 x 19-inch pan.
Layer with 1 pound ground meat (browned), 1 large onion (chopped) and 3 hot peppers (diced).
Spread remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: greg's favorite dip
directions: Take "softened" cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Add Miracle Whip and onion; mix together with electric beater.
Add milk until desired consistency.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine salad dressing, flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until thickened. Add Cheddar cheese; stir until melted.
Place potatoes in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish and pour sauce over potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add sugar and milk in nonstick pan.
Bring to boil, stirring. Boil approximately 5 to 7 minutes or until a drop in cold water is at soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla. Stir in peanut butter.
Mix until creamy. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool, cut and eat!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips and pour into casserole dish.
Top with potato chips and bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dates, cherries and pecans.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until set; when touched lightly, fingers leave no imprint.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate molasses cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add molasses.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to molasses mixture.
Mix flour with the cocoa and salt.
The eggs should be beaten and added last with the vanilla.
The flour-cocoa mixture can be added half at a time to the liquids and beaten in with a mixer, then add eggs.
It will be very soupy.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
It bakes best in a small tube pan (6 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch), greased and bottom lined with waxed paper.

title: pumpkin refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, pumpkin and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into roll, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter and about 8-inches long.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cut rolls into 1/8-inch slices.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes; cool.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook noodles and broccoli like normal in separate pans.

title: seafood cracker dip
directions: In a blender, combine nonfat cottage cheese, cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Remove from blender and mix in seafood.
Cover and chill.
Serve with nonfat saltine crackers. Yields 2 1/2 cups.
Makes ten 1/4 cup servings.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Cook until tender and take the skin off.
Pack into jars.
Leave small beets whole and quarter large ones.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and cook until sugar dissolves.
Add food coloring, if desired. Pour over beets and seal.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Melt margarine in 1 cup boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour.
Beat until frothy.
Add enough flour to make a sticky dough.

title: white house cheese rings
directions: Combine all ingredients and season with pepper, mix well and place in lightly greased mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: heavenly
directions: Combine and let stand 5 minutes the gelatin and 1/2 cup cold water.
Combine and bring to boil the sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Add gelatin and stir.
Cool and add pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill, then fold in whipped cream and pecans.
Take vanilla wafers and put in layers in loaf dish, then filling, then more vanilla wafers; have filling on top.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Layer half the potatoes and
half
the cheese in shallow buttered 2 quart casserole.
Repeat
layers.
In a bowl lightly beat eggs; stir in milk,
salt
and
nutmeg.
Pour
egg mixture over potatoes and cheese.
Bake
in
preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until
knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in nuts.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Put in refrigerator for several hours or overnight until firm.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top of mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni noodles and drain

title: diet vegetable stew
directions: Combine and simmer 2 hours.
One cup equals 20 calories.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and make into a loaf.
Glaze with brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and water.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours using a lid.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: eggless devil's food cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Rub in the shortening as for pies.
Add vanilla.
Add the milk.
Mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: luscious pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, and cloves.
Beat together sugar, oil and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin, and blend well. Add dry ingredients alternately to pumpkin mixture with water, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9-by-5-by-3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool on racks.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, lemon juice and onion.
Mix with electric mixer.
Spread in serving dish (such as large Pyrex pie pan), then spread chili sauce over top. Cover with chopped crabmeat and then sprinkle with parsley flakes. Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: german-fried vegetables
directions: Toss all vegetables with equal amounts of flour and cornmeal. Fry as you would fry okra, using half shortening and half margarine.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown beef with peppers and onions in a skillet.
Mix corn bread according to directions on box.
Add can of corn.
Mix together.
Heat large skillet or iron fry pan, oiled, in a 400° oven until hot.
Put in meat mixture, then a layer of the cheese and then top off with corn bread mixture.
Bake as directed on corn bread package.
Cut into wedges and serve.
This serves 6 to 8. Good with tossed salad and pinto beans.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix in blender the Oreos until like cornmeal.
Add 1/4 cup of sugar and 1 stick melted oleo.
Mix by hand.
Reserve 3/4 cup for topping.
Put remainder in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook 6 yellow crook-neck squash in salted water until tender (15 minutes or so) and divide in 2 portions.
In bottom of casserole dish, place a layer of crumbled Ritz crackers. Next layer is 1/2 of cooked squash mixed with soup, onion and egg. Next layer is cream cheese, cut in small pieces.
Next layer is remaining squash.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until heated through.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Follow basic brownie mix recipe.
Where it calls for 1 or 2 eggs, just use the egg whites.
Where it calls for oil, substitute equal amount of applesauce.
Brownies are great and cholesterol free!

title: vivian's chili verde
directions: Brown meat at medium to high heat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until meat is very tender.
Serve with flour tortillas.

title: apricot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl. Mix well. Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix together all other ingredients and add to chopped broccoli.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: oriental turkey salad
directions: Combine the turkey with the vegetables in a salad bowl.
Mix the oil, soy sauce and vinegar in a cruet until well blended.
Toss with the turkey mixture.
This makes a lovely light lunch for 4 to 6 people.
It is also a perfect way to use up extra turkey after the holidays.
Serve with a specialty bread.

title: pistachios depueblo
directions: Puree jalapeno peppers to measure 2 cups.
Puree onions and garlic together to measure 1 cup.
Combine to jalapeno pepper puree and the onion puree has been forced into the cracked shell openings as possible.
Dry in dehydrator for 24 hours or until crisp.
Or dry in oven at 150-175 degrees until pistachios are dried.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Bring rhubarb to a boil in water.
Reduce heat; add tapioca, salt, sugar, orange juice and rind.
Stir until sugar dissolves and rhubarb comes to a boil.
Cook over low heat until rhubarb is soft and tapioca is cooked.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: seven can soup
directions: Cook in slow cooker while at church, about 2 1/2 hours.
Serve over nacho chips.
Oh, don't forget to salt to taste.

title: sausage-cheese brunch dish
directions: Spread sausage in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Cut in squares to serve.

title: ham loaf
directions: Soak graham crackers in milk.
Mix with meat; add pinch of salt.
Baste ham loaf with brown sugar, water, vinegar and dry mustard.
Baste often during baking.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Place in layers on bottom of greased 10-inch pie plate the zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese.
Over this pour this mixture blended well: milk, Jiffy baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: dump cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift together the dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until blended, but do not beat.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 75 to 80 minutes. Cake will crack slightly on top.
Cool in pan on a rack.
Remove; serve plain or dusted with confectioners sugar.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice very thin the apples.
If apples lack tartness, sprinkle with about 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and dash of salt; mix well with apples.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with apple mixture; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust, cutting slits for escape of steam; seal.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Leave potatoes out of freezer about 15 minutes and then pound package until potatoes are separated.
Don't thaw out too much. Mix all together.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and drizzle on 1 stick butter or margarine.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Beat until mixed and add carrots.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: courthouse potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes. Cool and grate into large casserole. Add oleo (save 2 to 3 tablespoons for top), soup and onions to sour cream. Mix all together. Sprinkle cheese on top. Add reserved oleo to cereal. Sprinkle on top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy reuben sandwich
directions: Makes one serving.
Spread dressing on one side of each slice of toast.
Top one slice of toast with corned beef, sauerkraut and Swiss cheese.
Cover with remaining toast, dressing side down. Place 1 Bounty microwave on counter with sandwich diagonally in center.
Fold as directed for Bounty sandwich fold.
Place folded side down on microwave-safe plate.
Microwave at 70% (Medium-high) for 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through and cheese melts.

title: chicken with noodles casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water, until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Mix soup, milk and salt, heat, stirring constantly. Add cheese, stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup of the almonds and the bread crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Pour mixture over noodles.
Top with crumbs and almonds. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Place pieces into greased cake pan.
Melt butter and stir in other ingredients.
Pour over biscuits.
Top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pork roast and sauerkraut
directions: Brown roast; sprinkle with salt and pepper and add water and onion.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
About 1/2 hour before meat is done, add remaining ingredients.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pack in a sheet cookie pan or into a 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ratatouille of roasted vegetables
directions: Meaty shiitake and oyster mushrooms give this dish a hearty texture.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in flour, salt and soda until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: marinated pork strips
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Combine ingredients, except for oil, in a bowl.
Marinate pork strips in this mixture for at least 4 hours (or overnight).
Drain and reserve marinade.
Transfer to oiled baking dish and roast at 350° for 45 minutes.
Simmer marinade and serve with pork.
Serves 4.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, nuts and cocoa, mixing well.
Stir in corn syrup and bourbon; blend thoroughly.
Set aside in refrigerator for several hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Makes 36 Bourbon Balls.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt chips in top of a double boiler; stir until blended and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add walnuts and chow mein noodles; gently stir until evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread and bacon into bowl.
Add tomatoes, peppers and onion.
Mix all together with mayonnaise.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Mix chicken, soups, broccoli and cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Prepare Jiffy corn muffin mix as listed on box and spread over the top.
Bake until cornbread is brown and done.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with grated chocolate.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt almond bark.
Pour in pretzels.
Stir to coat.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Add peanuts, raisins and M&M's.
(M&M's should be pressed into stack after dipping; will melt and run.) Kids love to do this one!

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Combine vegetables and grains with gravy.
Top with a layer of instant potatoes and water.
How much depends on the size of pan. Bake in 350° oven until warm.
Top with paprika.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix together and place in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Let cranberries and sugar set for 15 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin with 1 cup hot water.
Then add the 1/2 cup cold water. Refrigerate until partially set.
Add fruit and vegetables.
Put in molded pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: billie's blueberry dessert
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Add pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: wiki-wiki cake(hawaiian for hurry up)
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into 9 x 12-inch pan.
(You can use fruit cocktail, also.)
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Dot with butter (cut into small pieces and place on top).
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: chili casserole
directions: Place 2 cups tortilla chips in a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of cheese soup over chips.
Spread chili over soup and top with remaining soup.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining chips and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt cheese and butter in a medium saucepan.
Add wine.
Heat thoroughly.
Add crabmeat.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: corned beef 'n cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute cabbage, celery and onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for about 5 minutes on high. Gradually add all ingredients, mixing well. Grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet or jelly roll pan (nonstick).

Pour batter into pan; smooth evenly. Sprinkle chopped nuts over batter. Bake in oven at 300° for 15 minutes. Remove immediately and roll while warm in a clean dish towel sprinkled (especially in center) with 10x sugar. Cool 1 hour. (Dish towel needs to be cotton or any clean piece of cotton about the size of dish towel will do.)

title: snow grapes
directions: Wash grapes.
Take off stems and drain well.
Lay on paper towels while mixing other ingredients.
Blend together cream cheese and sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Pour over grapes and stir.
Refrigerate.

title: baked pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, mix with flour and sugar. Melt margarine. Stir in crushed crackers, layer in casserole dish; 1/2 crackers, mixture, cheese, 1/2 crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blender potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, in hot oil, saute celery, onion and garlic until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Pour half the mixture into blender and puree until smooth. Repeat with remaining soup.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Yields 8 cups.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
Let set about 2 hours and refrigerate.
(Before refrigerating, take out garlic buttons.)

title: pea casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add drained peas, salt and pepper.
Chop eggs and add to peas.
Spread soup over top of mixture.
Heat at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When bubbly on top, add onions and heat for another 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: hamburger rice dish
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and green pepper.
Cook rice. Combine
soup,
mushrooms, meat and rice.
Simmer for a few minutes until it warms through,
then serve.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Roll into balls and bake at 350° to 400° for 17 minutes.
When cold, roll in confectioners sugar.
May have to double roll in sugar.

title: marinade sauce for grilled steak
directions: Pour over steak and marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Turn occasionally.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix and cook Jiffy mix as directed on box.
Cool corn bread, then crumble.
Mix all the other ingredients real well with the corn bread.
Let stand 30 to 45 minutes and then serve.

title: pizza lovers salad
directions: Toss all vegetables.
Mix dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese and croutons.

title: spinach-rice casserole
directions: Bring rice and 3 cups water to a boil, then cover and on lowest possible heat, simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from heat and fluff with fork.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat the butter or margarine or oil in a deep skillet.
Saute onion until soft.
Add spinach, salt and garlic; stir frequently over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Add this to rice, along with seasonings and half of sunflower seeds; mix well.
Optional:
Beat together eggs and milk and stir into rice mixture along with cheese.
Spread into prepared pan, sprinkle with remaining sunflower seeds and dust with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes until heated through and lightly browned on top.

title: stir fry rice
directions: Heat 2 tbsp. oil. Stir-fry meat until done. Add onion, corn and egg. Fry 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat. Heat 6 tbsp. oil; fry rice and add rest of mixture.

title: quick bar cookies(from mix)
directions: Prepare mix according to package directions.
Spread dough into ungreased 8 or 9-inch round baking dish.
Heat at Medium 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes.
To complete, let stand, covered, until cool.
Store, covered, until ready to serve.
Yields 16 bars.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion and oleo.
Mix well.
Put in dish and bake 30 minutes uncovered at 350° to 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and beef.
Mix with cream cheese.
The mixture will be stiff.
Use your hands to form in a ball.
Serve with Town House crackers.
Makes a pretty cheese ball for the Christmas holiday.

title: donna's hush puppies(great with fried catfish)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg and enough buttermilk to make a thick batter.
(Start with about 3/4 cup buttermilk.)
Drop by teaspoons into hot grease until golden brown.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart saucepot, in hot oil, brown roast on all sides. Spoon off fat.

title: peanutty chews
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheets.
In large saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until completely melted. Stir in peanuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Cool until firm.
Store, covered, in refrigerator in single layer.
Makes about 32 patties.
Preparation Time:
20 minutes plus cooling.

title: pizza crust
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Dissolve yeast in water. Mix in other ingredients. Let dough rest for 10 minutes. Spread on greased pizza pan. Pizza toppings can be added now, but I let the dough rest another 10 minutes and bake for 5-10 minutes before adding toppings. Bake completed pizza until cheese is melted and crust is golden brown.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pie dish.
Brown ground beef.
Mix sauce and ground beef.
Pour on top of cream cheese. Spread Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Bake the pie crusts until medium brown and let cool. Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and spread in bottom of cooled pie shells. Lay sliced peaches over mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon. Mix 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and water; cook until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin. Pour mixture over peaches and cool. Serve with whipped topping.

title: pineapple quickie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and then add eggs and pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add peanut butter.
Break in the eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and flavoring.
Make into tiny balls the size of bird eggs and place on baking sheet. Press flat with fork, making crisscross pattern.
Bake quickly at 350° to 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring to boil the first 3 ingredients. Stir until well mixed.
Mix in next 7 ingredients.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except egg whites and mix well.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites into mixture. Steam bake 60 minutes.
Unmold on serving plate and serve with creamed pea sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: noodle dish(buttered casserole)
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix cheese, onion and butter.
Pour
cooked noodles over this.
Mix in sour cream, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and put in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: overnight pickles
directions: Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cukes and onions in large bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Put in jars next day.
Keeps well if refrigerated for months.

title: bow tie pasta
directions: In a skillet or saucepan, saute the garlic in oil until golden. Now add the strips of chicken and saute until cooked.
Push the chicken to one side of the pan and add the broccoli florets.
Saute the broccoli until they are crisply tender.
Now, add the sun-dried tomatoes, the seasonings, white wine and the chicken broth.
To complete the sauce, add the butter, cover and simmer for 5 minutes over low flame.
Remove from heat.
Now add the cooked pasta and toss.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serves 4. Recipe can be doubled, if necessary.

title: helen powell's washington cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel and rinse eggs. Slice eggs lengthwise. Put egg yolks in bowl; use fork to mash until chunks are gone. Add rest of ingredients except paprika. Mix until desired texture. Fill egg whites with mixture, about 1 tablespoon each. Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: orange salad
directions: Mash oranges with fork and mix well with dry gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in dish and refrigerate until set.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon.
Bring to a full boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.

title: meatballs and spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients except salad oil and tomato sauce. Shape into balls of desired size.
Brown in vegetable oil; dip out and drain.
Add tomato sauce; simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: veal paprika
directions: Use pepper rings and sliced tomatoes for garnish.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Cool.
Add 3 eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate bits.
Spread into greased 19 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: basic white sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add evaporated milk and water, all at once. Continue to cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil 1 additional minute or until thick.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cottage cheese, sour cream, cream cheese, and taco seasoning together in a bowl.
In a 9 X 13-inch pan, spread refried beans, then add hamburger.
Add cottage cheese mixture on top of hamburger.
Shred lettuce and put on top, followed by cucumber, tomato, and shredded cheese.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Cook until they bubble.

title: old-time fudge
directions: Line a 10-inch square pan with foil; extend foil over edges of pan.
Butter foil; set aside.

title: tuna and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes 10 minutes. Melt butter in double boiler. Stir in flour, then mustard. Add milk, salt and pepper. In greased casserole, arrange potatoes, tuna and onions alternately. Pour sauce and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the first three ingredients well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Add Kraft garlic cheese with hot broccoli so it melts.
Add cream of mushroom soup, celery and onion.
Season to taste with Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce. Serve in heated casserole dish with corn chips.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Mix sour cream and sugar; spread on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Mix dry pudding with pineapple (including juice).
Add Cool Whip and blend very well.
Good on any flavor cake.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add oleo; mix well.
Make into 1-inch balls (chill 15 minutes).
Melt the chocolate chips with the paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate; place on wax paper.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in pan.
Roll biscuits and fill with apples.
Sprinkle apples with favorite spice (cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg).
Fold biscuit over and crimp edges.
Place in pan.

title: calico corn relish
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon into 1-quart jar.
Cover tightly and chill, turning jar occasionally, 4 hours or overnight.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and peppers.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add Certo and remove from heat.
Add coloring.
Let cool until thick.
Place in sterilized jars.

title: canned baked beans with  bacon or frankfurters
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place beans in a greased shallow ovenproof dish.
Cover the top with bacon or skinned sliced frankfurters.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. In a medium sized mixing bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy. Beat in condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla and stir until well mixed.
Pour into the crust.
Chill several hours and then top with cherry pie filling.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil on medium heat for 1 1/2 minutes while stirring.
Take off heat and mix in peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper; cool.

title: "hello dolly" delights
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in processor until very fine.
Butter sides of an 11 x 7-inch pan and place remaining butter in pan and melt.
Sprinkle wafer crumbs evenly over bottom.
Spread as evenly as possible in separate layers the coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Dribble condensed milk over layered mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 8 hours, preferably overnight.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Will keep 1 week in sealed container.

title: chocolate caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs and melted butter.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
In heavy saucepan, melt caramels with evaporated milk over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Top with pecans.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in chocolate.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream and pecans if desired.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add dry onion soup mix to meat. Add chili powder and garlic powder to meat.
Mix with liquids and simmer.

title: spinach and cheese medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3-quart casserole.
Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain well.
Mix spinach, eggs, onion, soup, butter and cheese together in a large bowl.
Mix in 2 1/2 cups croutons.
Place in casserole and top with remaining croutons. Bake 1 hour.

title: cajun catfish
directions: Combine salt, pepper and hot sauce to create marinade.
Season catfish with salt and pepper to taste and marinate for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Put cornmeal into paper bag.
Drop catfish in bag, one at a time, and shake bag until fish are completely coated. Fry fish in deep, hot olive oil (375°) until fish floats to surface and are golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Slice and coarsely chop large pieces of cauliflower and broccoli.
Combine cauliflower, broccoli and onion in a large bowl. In another bowl, beat together the Green Goddess dressing, mayonnaise, vinegar and celery seed; pour over vegetables.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mama's cheese dreams
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on a paper towel.
Combine mayonnaise and butter.
Stir in cheese, onion and cayenne pepper until well blended.
Gently stir in bacon.
Spread mixture on slices of bread.
Place on buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bread is golden brown.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In casserole, put in cubed chicken with sour cream and soup. Mix crumbs with butter and poppy seed.
Put on top.
Serves about 5.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add the sugar, then flour and vanilla. Mix well with hands, if necessary. Add nuts.
Pinch dough.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown.
Put into sack of powdered sugar to coat.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk together.
Will be very thick. Fold in Cool Whip.
Add oranges.
Use 1/2 package of cookies.
Add to mixture.
Store in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 1/2 minute (or until mixed well), scraping sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan or 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Saute onions and green pepper.
Combine cheese and flour. Place in pie crust.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix all ingredients and only half can of onions. Garnish with the other half of onions.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°
until bubbly.

title: our favorite bread
directions: Stir together sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and the 3 cups water until dissolved.
Now add the yeast and let set until yeast starts to work.
Then add the salt, oil and flours.
Mix well and knead until smooth.
Put tea towel over bowl and stick in oven with pilot on.
When about doubled in size, form loaves and lay on cookie sheet.
Let rise again, then knead again; put in pans.
Let rise and bake.

title: brown bread
directions: Boil raisins and water until raisins swell.
Cream together shortening, sugar and salt.
Add egg and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add cooled raisins and water to mixture.
Add flour. Mix and pour into 3 (3 ounce) vegetable cans, about 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Add nuts or candied fruit if desired.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla. Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filing before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Drain fruit cocktail, pineapple and cherries.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Serves 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Whip the whipping cream and add a little powdered sugar.
Mix all together.
It is better to be made and let mellow overnight.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or mixer and mix until smooth (sometimes it is thicker than at other times).
Store in refrigerator; use in any recipe calling for sweetened milk.
Makes 1 1/4 cups equal to one (14 ounce) size can.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl and stir.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours before serving, stirring occasionally.

title: granola
directions: Mix brown sugar, oil and honey in a saucepan.
Heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Combine dry ingredients in a large cake pan. Pour sugar mixture and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Let cool and add raisins, dates, nuts, etc.

title: pineapple bran bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Pour pineapple juice over bran and let stand 15 minutes.
Add nuts, pineapple, egg and shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix until blended.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and chill.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon until almost brown; add onion and sauce.
Add rice and coat it with the fat.
Mix tomato sauce, water and
spices. Pour over rice mixture.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Cover and simmer until done, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole americana
directions: Beat sour cream and cream cheese in a large bowl until blended.
Add hot potatoes; beat in milk and garlic, gradually beating until light and fluffy.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon potatoes into a 2-quart casserole; dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until brown. Makes 10 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour milk in pan, add salt and rice (washed).
Bring to boil, lower heat and cook for 2 hours, stirring often.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add some cooked rice to egg mixture.
Mix well. Pour into remainder of rice, mix well and add medium cream.
Put in oblong pan, top with cinnamon.

title: egg nog(12 servings)
directions: Beat egg yolks until stiff and light yellow. Slowly add 1/2 cup sugar, beating well.
Add alcohol.
Mix well and pour into punch bowl.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and jello in warm water.
Stir in orange juice, pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Add more sugar, if needed.
Lemons may be sliced to garnish the top of punch in punch bowl.

title: sausage snacks italiano
directions: Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal. Combine cheese and oregano. Sprinkle over dough.
Cut each rectangle crosswise to form 2 squares.
Place a sausage link on each square.
Roll up.
Cut each roll into 3 to 4 pieces. Secure each with a toothpick.
Place, cut side down, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Yields 2 dozen appetizers.

title: wonder chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish skin side up. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch lightly greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add water.
Cook until clear, then remove from heat.
Add dry jello.
Stir in well.
Line pie shell with strawberries.
Fill with cooked mixture.
Chill in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip when served.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over nuts, dates and raisins. Let cool. Mix remaining ingredients with water, dates and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan about 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: vegetable toss
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients (except lettuce and croutons), toss to blend.
Arrange on lettuce leaves, top with Pepperidge Farm cheese and garlic croutons.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 7 baked potatoes
directions: In a pan with a little butter, put green onions.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except potatoes, hot sauce, Velveeta cheese and ham; heat until hot.
Add a layer of potatoes, hot sauce, Velveeta cheese and some diced ham.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Twenty minutes before done, put Cheddar cheese on top.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots; drain and cool.
Place sliced onion, pepper and carrots in layers in dish.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 1/4 cup milk, sugar, salt and 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Heat until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°. Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in milk mixture, 1 1/2 cups flour and egg.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining 3/4 cup flour.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in well-greased bowl, turning to grease the top.
Cover to let rise in warm place (85°) free from drafts for 1 hour.
(Dough will not quite double in bulk.)

title: asparagus delight
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving 1 cup liquid; set aside.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add 1 cup asparagus liquid and milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown
sausage;
drain.
Separate
crescent
rolls
and press out in a 12-inch pizza pan to form crust.
Spoon sausage over crust,
sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese. In a bowl,
beat
together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.	Pour into crust.
Sprinkle
Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Crush cookies (reserve 1 1/2 cups for top). Combine cookies with melted oleo.
Mix and press lightly into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring water and bouillon to a rapid boil.
Add eggs; stir constantly for 1 minute.
Add onions and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Goes great with stir-fry.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown for 25 minutes.
Cut in pieces 2 x 1-inch.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Start the frosting 15 minutes before cake is done and all will be done at same time.

title: light velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave:
Cook Velveeta light cheese product and salsa or tomatoes and chilies in a 1 1/2-quart bowl on High 5 minutes or until Velveeta light cheese product is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Cooking time is 5 minutes.

title: mom's tomato gravy
directions: Put tomatoes on to boil.
Combine butter and flour in skillet. Add some canned milk right away.
Take pan of tomatoes off burner.
Add baking soda and add to gravy mixture.

title: paella a la caiolla
directions: Cut lobster's claws from the body and cut the body into pieces. Peel raw shrimp.
Clean the clams, mussels and crab's claws.
Put 3 tablespoons of olive oil in a pan.
Saute chicken, ham and pork over medium heat until golden brown.
Set aside; keep covered.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice using package directions.
Saute onion in margarine. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Spread 1 cup sauce in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagne; top with some sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat, gently pressing lasagne pieces into cheese mixture below.
End with lasagne, then pour remaining sauce, being careful to cover all lasagne pieces.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbly.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef in soup pot, stirring until brown and crumbly; drain.
Add tomato sauce, water and chili mix.
Mix well. Bring to a simmer. Stir in spaghetti.
Simmer, covered, for approximately 1 hour.

title: black beans
directions: Mix vegetables and fruit.
Combine spices, juice and oil in another bowl.
Toss the two together well.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with grilled shrimp.
Yum!

title: chocolate-cherry squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl combine flour, butter and brown sugar.
Blend on low speed to form fine crumbs, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Reserve 3/4 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Pat remaining crumbs into ungreased square pan,
9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in enough milk to make soft dough.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan, except pecans.
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes over moderate flame.
Let cool for a few minutes and then beat until creamy; add pecans and continue stirring until ready to pour into buttered platter.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake on cookie sheet.
While cake bakes, simmer sugar and pineapple.
After cake is done, punch holes and pour on the pineapple and sugar.
Chill.
Make pudding and add coconut.
Pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip, then the pecans.

title: turkey vegetable soup
directions: Simmer turkey necks, onion, celery, salt, pepper, rosemary and bay leaves in water for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove necks.
Cool. Strip meat from the bones.
Reserve turkey meat.
Spoon off fat. Bring broth to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes, carrots and rice. Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Add beans and corn.
Now add everything together and cook for 10 to 20 minutes, until vegetables and rice are tender.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients well, then add remaining ingredients. Stir and enjoy.

title: spicy walnut-raisin pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, spices, corn syrup and margarine with hand beater.
Stir in walnuts and raisins. Pour into pastry lined plate.
Bake until filling is set, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef.
Stir in tomato sauce and heat. Cook noodles as in directions; drain and mix with 1 teaspoon butter.
Combine cheeses, onion and pepper.
Butter 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Line with half of the noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Add rest of noodles.
Pour melted butter over top, then pour meat mixture over all.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffed mirlitons
directions: Boil the mirlitons in lightly salted water until a testing fork will pierce them all the way through (without using excessive force).
Then remove them from the water and set aside to cool.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Pour half the mixture into a dish and let congeal.
Spread one whole carton of sour cream on top of the congealed salad.
Pour the other half of mixture on top and let set until congealed.
Chill and serve.

title: jefferson's chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter on High; add green pepper and mushrooms. Microwave on High 2 minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add chicken and microwave on High 5 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Skin chicken and place in large shallow baking dish.
Combine salad dressing, soup mix and apricot preserves and blend thoroughly.
Pour the mixture over chicken.
