Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, basting occasionally with pan drippings.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve with rice or wild rice and the pan drippings.

title: jello cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, Jell-O, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; blend well.
By teaspoonful roll in balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Press each dough ball with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes. Cool slightly before removing to cooled rack.

title: chewy squares
directions: Step 1:
Mix cake mix, 1 cup of peanut butter, 1 stick of butter and 1 egg.
Form into a dough.

title: noodle soup
directions: Combine broth and tomato sauce. Bring to a boil. Add noodles and cook until noodles are tender.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and the shortening and sweet potatoes while hot.
Combine potato mixture.
Knead for 1 minute.
Roll or pat to 3/4-inch thickness. Cut and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tangy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in freezer until slushy.
Can freeze in ice tray for cubes.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: liver ball
directions: Saute butter and diced onion.
Combine with liver and seasonings; steam 1/2 hour.
Add eggs and mayonnaise.
Shape into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix dry starch and 1/2 cup water.
Add boiling water.
Stir rapidly.
Pour in soap powder and stir until smooth.
Add tempera paint and food coloring for color.
Store in tight lidded container.
Makes 2 cups.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, vanilla, almond flavor and eggs. Beat and cream well.
Add flour and milk to make a soft dough. Put in bowl with a lid and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna, soup, peas and noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: russian dill pickles
directions: In each clean sterilized jar, place 1 head fresh dill, 2 slices onions, 1 clove garlic and fresh cucumbers to fill. To make brine, mix vinegar, water, sugar and pickling salt.
Bring to a boil and pour over pickles in jars.
Seal jars and let sit for a week before using.

title: deluxe squash casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper. Add squash. Simmer 15 minutes. Add rice, salt, cubes and water. Put in casserole. Top with cheese. Heat.

title: party chicken
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with dried beef. Wrap chicken breasts with bacon.
Place on top of beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275°
for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: chocolate milk shake or malt
directions: In a blender combine the ingredients and process for about 30 seconds, or until well mixed and frothy.
Pour into a tall glass and serve immediately with a straw.
Garnish with nutmeg, if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk. Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts. Blend well.
Pour into greased pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease oblong cake pan.
Put in crushed pineapple.
Add cherry pie filling.
Dump the box of cake mix.
(Do not mix up.)
Add pecans.
Dot the butter on top of this.
Do not mix any, just put each article on top of each other.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: seared sea scallops with basil mashed potatoes and chanterelle(serves 1)
directions: Mashed Potatoes:
Cook potato until soft, then whip until fluffy, adding milk and butter for creaminess.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pick basil off stems.
Blanch quickly and then cool off in ice water.
Squeeze water out and blend with olive oil in blender until you have a puree.
Add 1 tablespoon of puree to potato; mix well.

title: cranberry sherbet
directions: Simmer cranberries in water until soft.
Put in blender and grind.
Add sugar and pineapple juice; boil, covered, for 5 minutes, without stirring.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix together and spread with 1/3 cup of mayo.
Chill; stir in mayo when ready to serve.

title: streusel topping for fruit pies
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle over pies and bake.

title: spiced carrots
directions: Boil carrots (if you want them crisp, don't boil too long). Drain carrots.
Mix all ingredients in a large container. Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: ham loaf
directions: If using tomato juice, use 1/2 cup bread crumbs.

title: cold dough
directions: Mix flour and margarine into crumbs like pie crust.
Add sour cream and egg yolk.
Mix well.
Put on floured wax paper and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and curry powder in saucepan; heat, stirring until well blended.
Combine fruit in shallow 2-quart casserole and add sauce.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beat after each.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour and milk a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Put in cold oven.
Set heat at 325°.
Bake for 80 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pudding pie
directions: Crumble graham crackers and spread in a 9-inch pie pan.
Make pudding according to directions.
When pudding is almost set, pour over graham crackers.
Refrigerate pie until completely set. Drain peaches and place on top.
Decorate with whipped topping. Serves 8.
Contains 126 calories and 2 fat grams.

title: edith harris' fudge pie
directions: Mix together and spread in pie plate.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat the eggs.
Stir in the
oil, vanilla and sugar.
Add in the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Flatten with the greased bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the chicken broth, chicken soup and peas and carrots.
Place sliced, boiled eggs on top of the chicken.
Pour broth, soup and vegetables over the eggs and chicken.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, eggs, butter and vanilla well. Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm.

title: apricot cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch rounds.
Cut hole in center of 1/2 of rounds.
Place round on cookie sheet. Top with filling, almost to the edge.
Place round with hole in center on jam.
Press edges together.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: garlic dressing
directions: Combine ingredients into jar and shake.
Chill and serve over favorite salad.

title: peanutty cocoa bonbons
directions: In a large bowl, beat together cream cheese and milk until fluffy.
Blend in next 3 ingredients.
Stir in nuts, if desired. Cover and let chill several hours or until firm enough to handle. Shape cocoa mixture into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on a waxed paper lined tray and refrigerate, uncovered, for 3 to 4 hours or until dry.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a Bundt pan or tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with 1/4 c. milk.
Cool.
Fold in 1 c. whipped cream.
Then fold in 1 pint of whichever fruit you desire. Put in Graham cracker crust and let cool.

title: chocolate golf balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and form into balls around cherry in center of each piece.
Roll in coconut.
Place in cool place until set.

title: mystery pie
directions: Whip the egg whites; add sugar and baking powder.
Fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Butter a 9-inch pan.
Put mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or a little less.
Cover pie with whipped cream; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cut in wedges.

title: cooked pimiento and cheese
directions: Heat and stir cheese and milk until blended; add vinegar, sugar, pimiento and egg.
Cook until slightly thick, about 15 to 20 minutes, continuously stirring.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise.
This recipe makes about 1-quart and will keep indefinitely in covered jar in refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix sour cream and vanilla.
Add sugar to taste.
Either use as a dip or pour over cut fruit.

title: meatball soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Form into small meatballs and brown.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add meatballs.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim round steak (not tenderized) and cut into bite-size pieces.
Put into bowl with tight cover.
Add sliced onion and pepper.
Add garlic powder, seasoning salt, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Cover bowl; shake and put in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours.

title: pizza pie
directions: Combine hash browns, salt, pepper and oil.
Pat into 9-inch greased pie plate to form shell.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 500°.
Brown beef and onion (if using fresh onion); pour off drippings.
Sprinkle in flour and rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add gradually to eggs.
Stir butter and cocoa in saucepan over low heat until butter is melted.
Beat slowly into egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans and vanilla. Pour into shallow 9x9 greased pan and place in larger pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be served warm or cool, with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: gourmet sweet-hot spread
directions: Mix together dry mustard and cider vinegar; let stand overnight.
Beat together and cook until thickened in double boiler the vinegar-mustard mixture, eggs, sugar and salt.
Cool, then beat in mayonnaise.
Makes about 1 quart.
Store in glass jar in refrigerator.
Great on hot dogs, burgers, pork roast, turkey sandwiches, etc.
We use it instead of boughten mustard!

title: brownies
directions: Mix eggs lightly.
Stir in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Set aside. Melt cocoa, shortening and oil.
Add egg mixture.
Add flour and nuts.
Do not beat at any time.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Put stuffing in middle of steak.
Roll up and hold together with toothpick.
Put in roasting pan.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: caraway carrots and potatoes*(quick and easy)
directions: Wash potatoes; do not peel.
Heat butter in saucepan and add onion.
Saute briefly; add carrots, potatoes, water, salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook about 12 minutes until potatoes and carrots are done (time varies, depending on size of veggies).
Serve sprinkled with parsley. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in a greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 3/4 of crushed cookies.
Mix together Cool Whip, butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk, vanilla and pudding.
Pour over cookies and top with remaining cookies.
Freeze or chill (either way, it's good).

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add all other ingredients.
Reserve enough cheese to sprinkle on top for the last 5 or 10 minutes of backing.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into two 9-inch graham cracker crusts.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: carrot pie
directions: Thoroughly combine carrots, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs, milk and evaporated milk and blend.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then in 325° oven about 45 minutes or until mixture does not adhere to knife.
Cool and top with whipped cream to serve.

title: lana's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture in casserole dish.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix cornbread with bread crumbs and add boiling stock.
Cover and set for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add chopped boiled eggs, celery, onion and bell pepper.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Since stock and bread are already seasoned, add salt and pepper only if desired.
Makes 8 cups.

title: mexican green chili squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 12 x 8-inch glass pan. Spread chopped green chilies on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle both cheeses over chilies.
Beat eggs; add milk and flour.
Mix until blended.
Add garlic powder, salt and hot sauce.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until set and brown.
Don't let edges brown too quickly; cover with tinfoil lip if necessary.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Can be kept warm in a 200° oven if wrapped in tinfoil.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly together.
Form ball and chill.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring chicken and water mixture to a boil.
Add onion, celery and carrots.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Discard bay leaves.

title: punch
directions: Mix liquids together and then top with sherbet.

title: tomato potato soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in a small amount of water until done (about 30 minutes).
Add potatoes, juice and salt.
Cook on low until potatoes are done.
Add half and half to desired consistency.
Add butter and serve.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/3 cup soup (undiluted), beef, bread crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties and brown.
Mix flour and remaining soup.
Then add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour mixture over patties.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 20 minutes.
Baste occasionally or in crock-pot for a couple of hours.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup, water, tomato sauce, kidney beans, sugar and chili powder.
Heat and serve.

title: kansas shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except beef until creamy.
Spread cheese mixture on separated dried beef slices and roll each up jelly roll fashion.
Chill well in foil wrap.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Spear each with a wooden cocktail pick.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make two layers starting with asparagus covering with the sauce made from the cheese, milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Put cracker crumbs on top; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and peas
directions: Cut chicken in 2-inch strips; brown in butter.
Add water, peas and Lipton soup.
Simmer until chicken is tender and gravy has thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water and mix.
Stir in Crisco, sugar, flour and salt and mix well.
Cover with towel and let rise for 30 minutes.
Grease 12 muffin tins.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into tins.
Cover and let rest another 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl; beat vigorously with a spoon or electric mixer at medium speed until smooth.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt. Add dry ingredients to oil mixture, mixing well.
Stir in coconut, carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until center of cake is firm to touch.
Cool in pan on rack.
Makes 16 servings.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine other ingredients.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and add moist ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: jezebel spread
directions: Mix gently with fork and re-pack in jars.
Refrigerate.
Serve over cream cheese and crackers.
Lasts indefinitely in refrigerator.
So good for last-minute hors d'oeuvre.

title: crank peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add to evaporated milk, Eagle Brand milk and 2 cups whole milk.
Heat over medium heat until hot, stirring constantly.
Pour in churn.
Add other ingredients.
Stir.
Crank according to churn instructions.

title: holiday dip
directions: Add milk to cheese gradually until smooth.
Add sour cream, beef, onion and peppers.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: family swiss steak
directions: Mix flour and mustard together.
Cut steak in approximately 2 x 3-inch squares.
Roll in flour and mustard mixture.
Pound steaks with tenderizing hammer.
In 6 to 8-quart saucepan, put in oil and brown steaks on each side.
Remove and set aside.
In same pan, add tomato sauce, onions, Worcestershire sauce, celery and brown sugar.
Bring to a slow boil.
Turn off and add meat and place in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain and serve.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Mix rye flour with hot water and molasses.
Add yeast to warm water.
Mix rye flour, water and molasses mixture with yeast and shortening.
Add flour.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Shape into 3 loaves.
Let rise again. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: energy drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend 2 minutes or until smooth.
Serve at once.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs, sour cream, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg until well mixed.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake below oven center in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Cut in shortening.
Mix in egg and bananas.
Add nuts and rolled oats.
Bake at 400°.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix and blend in flour and baking powder.
Bake 8 minutes at 375° or less after rolling and cutting with cutters.

title: mom's beef-noodle casserole
directions: Brown onion in skillet with margarine. Add meat and brown. Cook noodles in boiling, salted water.
Also cook celery in salted water.
Drain each.
Mix onion, meat mixture, celery and noodles with undiluted tomato soup.
Put in a shallow baking dish or casserole. Sprinkle grated cheese over the top and bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cherry peppercorn sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until sauce thickens and cherries are plump and tender. Serve with venison or lamb.

title: vivian's rice
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Cook rice.
Saute onion and celery in 1 to 2 tablespoons margarine until soft.
Mix vegetables and soup; add chiles.
Fold in rice sour cream and cheese (oblong baking dish).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash until tender.
Drain.
In baking dish, layer squash, dressing and soup.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle grated cheese on when nearly done.

title: johnny mazette
directions: In a large skillet, saute pepper, celery, onions and ground meat in very hot butter.
Add salt.
Reduce heat; cook 5 minutes. Stir in mushrooms and canned liquid soup and sauces.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix together and bake covered, no peeking, for 3 hours at 300°.
I use a cast-iron Dutch oven and have even made this using round steak rather than stew meat.
Great when mom's out branding and there's no one to man the kitchen stove.

title: applesauce meatloaf
directions: Mix together first six ingredients.
Shape into loaf or 2 inch balls.
Put in pan, add onion, peppers, tomatoes and brown sugar over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour for meatballs slightly longer for loaf.

title: special occasion chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat; add chicken and cook 10 minutes.
Turn chicken; add mushrooms and shallots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Transfer chicken to platter; sprinkle cheese over chicken.
Top with mushrooms and shallots.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields 4 servings.

title: peanut butter brownie cups
directions: Mix brownies according to package directions.
Fill paper lined or foil lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Remove wrappers from peanut butter cups; set one in each muffin cup and press down until batter meets the top edge of candy. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix together in blender, pour into gallon container and fill with cold water. Mix well. Freeze until slushy. Good for any occasion.

title: lemon tarragon dressing
directions: Combine in a jar with a cover.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In medium glass bowl, crumble ground beef.
Stir in onion. Heat 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes on High until beef is brown, stirring once, drain.

title: spinach 24 hour salad
directions: In glass bowl, layer spinach, bacon, eggs, lettuce, onion, and peas.
In separate bowl, mix together mayonnaise and Miracle Whip. Spread over peas.
Then sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Cube cream cheese and allow to warm to room temperature. Drain juice from pineapple. Add orange juice to pineapple juice until liquid equals 2 cups.
Heat juice to boiling.
Add Jell-O and cream cheese to hot liquid.
Beat with electric mixer until most of the cream cheese is dissolved.
Add fruit and pecans. Pour in 7-Up and stir lightly. Fold in marshmallows.
Pour mixture into large container and refrigerate until congealed. Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: hot baked potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and dry.
Heat oven to 400°.
Rub potatoes with salad oil. Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: fruit cake
directions: With mixer, beat margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Stir in pineapple with juice.
Roll all fruit and nuts with remaining 1 1/2 cups flour. Stir together all fruit and nuts so it will all be coated with flour.
Pour liquid mixture over fruit; mix well with spoon.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Place roast in center of double thickness of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle all sides of meat with dry onion soup mix.
Spoon can of mushroom soup on top.
Seal meat in foil. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Using a knife, cut cheese and butter into flour mixture.
Fill cookie press, star plate, and make long lines on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 10 minutes).

title: mom's stuffed green peppers with homemade creole sauce
directions: Sauce:
Saute green pepper, onion and garlic in oil.
Simmer 5 minutes until soft, not browned.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 40 to 50 minutes, until thick.
Add this mixture to 1 pound ground meat browned and sauteed with 1 tablespoon of grated onion and 1/3 cup finely chopped celery.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cool 5 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Add 1 1/2 cups cooked rice.
Moisten with Creole sauce, you may not want all of it.

title: chinese vegetable soup
directions: Fry turkey and onion together.
In large kettle, combine turkey with remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: easy turkey loaf
directions: In a small skillet saute onion and green pepper in oil for about 5 minutes.
Crumble bread into bowl.
With fork beat in eggs, seasonings and 1/3 cup spaghetti sauce.
Stir in onion and pepper mixture.
Add turkey and with hands, mix lightly but thoroughly.
Pack into a 7 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Spread 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and let stand in pan about 10 minutes.
Lift out and set on small platter.
Garnish with parsley.

title: fish florentine
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs and basil.
Coat fillets with crumb mixture, pressing firmly.
In a large skillet, heat oil or spray with nonstick spray.
Brown fish on both sides.
Spoon cooked spinach evenly onto fish fillets and sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sugar free oatmeal cakeroswell, new mexico
directions: Pour 1 1/4 c. boiling water over 1 c. Quick oats.
Add 1 stick oleo and let stand 20 minutes.

title: chicken stew with dumplings
directions: *I use leftover turkey or chicken.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add 3/4 cup of the nuts. Combine the remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients. Stir only until the flour is moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts over the top of the loaf.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green peppered steak
directions: Brown steak in oil.
Add garlic, sugar and soy sauce.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, bean sprouts, green pepper and tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
(Do not overcook.)
Mix cornstarch with water and add to ingredients.
Cook until sauce is clear or thickened.
Sprinkle chopped green onions over mixture. Serve over rice with green salad and bread sticks.

title: cherry cheese miniatures
directions: Place wafers in paper baking cups.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix in sugar, juice and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well.
Spoon into cups.
Bake at 375° approximately 15 minutes.
Top with pie filling.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put beef in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each chicken breast.
Place chicken breasts on dried beef.
Mix together sour cream and soup.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: taco meat filling
directions: Brown beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Makes filling for 8 taco shells.

title: quick sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat corn oil in skillet.
Add pork and brown.
Add pineapple chunks, corn syrup, vinegar, catsup, soy sauce and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a separate dish, combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water.
Add to skillet with green pepper.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; add dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup bananas and 1/4 cup milk; beat 2 minutes.
Add remainder and beat.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Add last 4 ingredients.
This will be sticky.
Knead about ten times and pat out flat.
Cut with biscuit cutter.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch well in saucepan.
Add berry juice; cook, stirring, over medium heat, until thick and clear.
Add food coloring.
Spoon a few spoons of glaze in pie shell and spread thinly to coat crust.
Pile in fresh berries; pour remaining glaze over berries to cover.
Refrigerate two hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage well, stirring to crumble.
Drain on paper towels. Combine sausage and remaining ingredients and pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: classic fudge(real fudge!)
directions: *May substitute 2 squares baking chocolate for cocoa and oil.

title: potato lefse
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in salted water. Drain and mash well. (I rice them.)
Add cream, butter, salt and sugar.
Let mixture get cold.
Add 4 scant cups of flour.
Knead mixture until smooth. Roll out thin and bake on lefse pan.
Makes approximately 24 average lefses.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Heat and dissolve sugar, vinegar and oil.
Rinse all vegetables; once cut, place into bowl.
Spoon liquid over vegetable mixture.
Add garlic salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and sugar. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool completely; bring to boil pineapple juice. Add jello and strawberries. Chill until slightly set; set aside. Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy. Add Cool Whip and spread over. Top with strawberry mixture. Chill until ready to serve.

title: tuna mac and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart microwavable serving dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir casserole and continue heating on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Cool and then add rest of ingredients.
Stir together.
Spoon into small cups and freeze. Makes 36 cups.

title: garlic & cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine buttermilk baking mix, milk and cheese. Mix with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop dough by tablespoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8-10 minutes, or until golden brown. Combine melted margarine and garlic powder in a small bowl. Brush over biscuits before removing from cookie sheet. Serve warm.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks in a little cool milk and add to hot milk.
Boil until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Place in baked crust and top with meringue.

title: knox blocks(finger jello)
directions: In a large bowl, mix gelatine and flavored gelatin.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Pour into large, shallow 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: orange muffins
directions: Grease 18 muffin cups or line with paper.
Set aside.

title: bonbon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla. Work in flour until dough holds together.
(If dough is dry, mix in 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.)
Form balls with cherry center. Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Ice and decorate.

title: sofritto
directions: Chop hearts into 1/4-inch cubes.
Wash cubes in salt water. In 3-quarts of water, boil cubes for 45 minutes.
Drain cubes and set aside.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Put salmon into loaf pan; mash.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly. Melt margarine in heated milk.
Add to salmon; stir well.
Add cereal.
Bake about 1 hour at 375°.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix together the flour, butter and pecans until crumb like and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown at 350°, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Make a mixture of cream cheese, powdered sugar and half the whipped topping.
Mix well (whip) and spread over cooled crust.
For the top layer, mix pudding mixes with milk until smooth and thickened.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining whipped topping over top and sprinkle with the grated chocolate bar.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: tomato relish
directions: Peel and dice the tomatoes and onions.
Mix ingredients and put in a pot over medium heat for about an hour.
Put in a jar and seal.

title: cheese-rye appetizers
directions: Spread mixture on party rye slices.
Bake until bubbly (10 to 12 minutes) at 350°.

title: blueberry snow
directions: Crumble angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish. Mix cream cheese and milk together.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour over cake and chill 15 minutes.
Pour blueberry pie filling on top.

title: chili salad taco style
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain and rinse meat with hot water. Return meat to skillet and add the taco seasoning with enough water to dissolve the seasoning.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add the chili and beans.
Mix well.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.
Cream cheese frosting is good on this cake.

title: great-great aunt nola's casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers together in large bowl. In casserole dish, begin with vegetable mixture, alternating layers of vegetables and crushed crackers.
Top with crackers. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saut onions.
Add meat and brown.
Add green chilies, enchilada sauce and evaporated milk.
Spray 13 x 9 pan with Pam.
Layer tortillas in pan; add meat mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and bubbling.

title: quick skillet stew and dumplings
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet and drain excess fat. Add 1 can sauce, vegetables, water, salt, thyme and pepper. Combine well and bring to boil.
Mix together biscuit mix and milk.
Spoon around edge of boiling beef mixture in 5 or 6 mounds. Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Pour on remaining sauce.
Cover and simmer another 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: quick-n-hearty potato soup
directions: In medium saucepan, cook all ingredients on medium-high heat until boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, or until potatoes and celery are tender.

title: bbq meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the bbq sauce, until blended. Place in greased loaf pan. Top with BBQ sauce. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt the cube of margarine in heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour; cook a few minutes while stirring.
Slowly add milk and broth, stirring constantly.
Let soup come slowly to a low boil.
Saute broccoli pieces and chopped onion in 1 tablespoon margarine; add vegetables to the soup.
Add garlic and white pepper.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix ingredients together, except for pecans.
Mix in half of pecans.
Save half to roll cheese ball in.

title: black pepper ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put spareribs in a baking pan in a single layer.
Generously salt and pepper both sides of ribs.
Bake for 30 minutes on each side (1 hour total).
Serve right away.

title: peanut butter nuggets
directions: *Plain milk chocolate Hershey bar.

title: jerky
directions: Mix together and marinate for 2 hours.
Put meat in a dehydrator until thoroughly dry.
Time will depend on thickness of meat.
This is great to take for a snack on a fishing trip.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in container.
To use:
Place 1 - 3 teaspoons in cup.
Add boiling water and stir.

title: juan's sopapia
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together. Cut in Crisco and enough water to make a dry dough. Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut into 2-inch triangles. Deep-fry until light brown on both sides. Makes 4 dozen.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Cook the pork by frying it.
Chop up the meat.
Then put the meat in the oven to dry it out.
Then add it to the beans.
Add the bottle of barbecue sauce, Texas Pete, salt and pepper.
Cook 30 minutes to an hour on low heat.

title: harvest beef casserole
directions: Power Level: High (100%).
Cooking Time: 13 to 17 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugars, eggs and shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients, pumpkin and water.
Mix until well blended.
Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool on rack.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Blend flour, baking powder, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa in a bowl.
Stir in milk and shortening.
Blend in nuts.
Spread in square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
(During baking, cake mixture rises to the top and chocolate sauce settles to the bottom.)
Cut; invert.

title: cinnamon cheese squares
directions: Spread package of crescent rolls on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pinching seams together.
Don't put up sides of pan. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until smooth. Beat real good.
Spread over dough in pan.

title: crunchy taco bake
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole or medium bowl. Add onions.
Microwave at High, 4 to 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring to break apart after half the time.
Drain. Stir in chili with beans, tomato sauce, tomato paste, chili powder and salt.
Microwave at High, 6 to 8 minutes or until heated and flavors are blended.
Sprinkle 1 cup corn chips in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture over chips.
Top with remaining chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave at High, 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potato slices and package of seasoned sauce mix into 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to boiling.
Stir into potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: aunt edith's chicken
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Add chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting frequently.

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pie plate. In small mixer bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and butter.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to egg mixture, beating until smooth and blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla. Spread batter into prepared pie plate.
Bake 35 minutes or until set (pie will not test done in center). Cool completely and cut into wedges. Serve with ice cream and chocolate topping.

title: cranberry surprise pie
directions: In a 10-inch pie plate, spread cranberries. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and pecans; set aside.
In a bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer.
Gradually add remaining cup of sugar.
Beat well. Add butter, shortening and flour alternately to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture over cranberries.
Bake about 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, except 1/3 cup.
Sift sugar, flour and cocoa and salt.
Place in double boiler.
Stir remaining 1/3 cup milk into dry ingredients to form a smooth paste and pour into egg mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar to each egg white.
Put whites on pie and brown at 425°.

title: divinity salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar and egg yolks and pour over the marshmallows, pineapple and pecans.
Mix together, then fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together with hands.
Form small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
May be frozen and cooked later.

title: marta's fried catfish
directions: First clean the fish.
Cut the fish into filets.
Then sprinkle filets with garlic powder and salt.
Next, pour oil into frying pan and turn stove on to medium-high heat.
While the oil gets hot, put cornmeal in bowl and dip filets in cornmeal.	When oil is hot, fry the filets until golden-brown.
Serve catfish hot, with a salad.
Feeds 4 people.

title: lemon herb chicken
directions: Combine thyme, marjoram, celery salt, pepper and lemon juice. Sprinkle over chicken.
Roll chicken in flour.
Slowly brown chicken pieces in melted shortening, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes until tender.
Garnish with slices of lemon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter sandwiches
directions: Get 2 breads and take one bread and put the peanut butter on it and put the other one on top.
And cut it up and eat it.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles in boiling water.
When noodles are done, combine noodles, tuna, celery soup, mushroom soup and mushrooms in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Take out and top with cheese (grated) and favorite cracker crumbs.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Enjoy!

title: cola barbecue chicken
directions: Mix together cola and ketchup; set aside.
Wash chicken and put in a 10-inch skillet with a cover.
Add the cola mixture, pouring over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Sauce will thicken.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, green pepper, onion, carrots and celery seed. Add oil, vinegar, sugar, and salt to taste.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Cool. Shape into balls with buttered hands.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until soft.
Add everything (including the fat which adds much of the flavor) except the crawfish tails and simmer for 10 minutes, sprinkling the flour over the contents of the pan.

This is to give the sauce a little body, and you can add more if you like, but do not make a roux if you want your dish to be an authentic etouffee. Save the roux for the crawfish stew, another recipe entirely.
Now add the crawfish tails and simmer for 15 minutes.
For a light tomato taste, add a small can of V-8 juice.
Then it becomes a "Crawfish Ettouffee A La Tomate."

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in frying pan. Add flour and stir. Add whole milk and stir until thickened. Remove from heat. Add mustard, Old Bay, salt, pepper, onion, parsley flakes and chopped green pepper; mix and put in baking dish.

title: jack-o-lantern cheese spread
directions: Line 8-inch round cake pan with plastic wrap; lightly oiled. Process cheeses and salad dressing in food processor until well blended.
Spread cheese mixture into pan.
Cover and chill 2 hours or until firm.
Use ends of plastic wrap to remove cheese from pan and invert onto serving plate.
Smooth top and sides of cheese with small metal spatula.
Use a toothpick to draw outline of eyes, nose and mouth of Jack-O-Lantern.
Fill in outlines with black olives. Serve at room temperature.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields about 3 1/2 c. cheese spread.
Can also make a football for Super Bowl.
Use your own imagination!

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a double boiler, add oleo; melt.
Add chocolate until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix.
Cook until sugar is melted, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Use to make Hot Fudge Cake.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In a saucepan, blend chili beef soup and nacho cheese soup/dip or Cheddar cheese soup/sauce.
Slowly heat through, stirring often.
Garnish with sweet red and green pepper strips and sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
May be doubled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Pour into buttered casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly (approximately 30 minutes). Sprinkle browned and buttered bread crumbs over top.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mince salmon with fork.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Make in 2 loaf pans and grease pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake #2
directions: Beat together sugar and oil. Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with eggs, beating after each addition. Add vanilla, nuts and chopped apples. It will be a very stiff batter (but after it is cooked, it is a very moist, flavorful cake). You might have to stop the mixer when batter gets stiff (after apples and nuts are added) and use a wooden spoon to get it ready to pour in the pan. You may use tube pan but I prefer rectangular pan (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch metal).

title: creamy cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Bring water with bouillon cubes in to a boil.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
In separate pan, melt butter or margarine. Add flour, stirring constantly and cook for 2 minutes.
Add milk gradually.
When this begins to thicken, add to cooked vegetables and cook until thick.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Season to taste.
May add 1 to 2 cups chopped cooked ham for extra flavor.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: In a large pot boil sweet potatoes until done.
Boil with peelings left on and stick with fork to test when done.
Let cool, then carefully remove peeling.
Slice lengthwise and fry in black skillet with small amount of oil.
Fry until brown and put onto platter.
While hot, sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Continue frying and layering until all done.

title: zucchini-nut bread
directions: Note:
Substitute 1 cup mashed bananas for zucchini. Delicious banana bread.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon 3 times and set aside. In another bowl mix oil and sugar together, adding one egg at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour mixture to oil mixture and mix well.
Add apple and pecans, mix well.
Then add vanilla. Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix salt and mustard; add vinegar and stir.
Add garlic, parsley and oil.
Marinate cauliflower (in florets), onions and olives overnight.
Drain before serving and mix with shredded lettuce. Remove garlic and pour liquid over salad.

title: taco chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Take off bones.
Line baking pan with chips. Layer ingredients:
chicken, sauce, soup, onion, salt and pepper (keep some chips to put on top).
Pour broth on chips. Put grated cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pot roast with onions
directions: Slice onion.
Heat the oil in a large pot over medium heat; brown the meat on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Add onions, the stock, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook over low heat for about 2 hours.
Remove the meat to a platter; keep warm.
Skim the fat from the liquid.
Bring liquid to a boil; cook until reduced to 3 cups.
Slice the meat; serve it with the reduced broth as a sauce.

title: cool whip - chip treat
directions: Dunk cookie in milk and lay face down in casserole dish. Repeat until there is a complete layer of cookies.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip over cookie layer.
Repeat layering scheme until dish is full.
Cool for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve cold.
Enjoy!

title: party cocktail wieners
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and heat thoroughly.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Mix together soy sauce, garlic, vinegar, salt and pepper. Squeeze lemons in chicken and on the skins. Pour mixture over chicken and marinate one hour or longer depending on how strong you like the soy flavoring. Barbecue or bake chicken.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Cook 1/2 cup sugar in electric skillet, stirring constantly until golden brown.
Slowly add water, remaining sugar, vanilla and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Boil until all ingredients are dissolved. Mix last 6 ingredients together and drop by tablespoon in boiling liquid.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes on a medium to low heat. Serve hot or cold.
Excellent with vanilla ice cream.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat wok or saute pan.
Add oil and onions.
Saute onions until tender.
Add rice and saute.
Add beaten eggs and stir well. Season with soy sauce.
Saute until done.

title: chess pie
directions: *The sugar may be all white or part brown and part white (1 cup white and 1/2 cup brown, mixed, is better).

title: oyster crackers
directions: Place all ingredients in a plastic bag and mix.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Cook all just until dissolved.
Pour over popped corn and form balls.
If too sticky, dip hands in water to form balls.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place ingredients in order given in layers in buttered baking dish. Season each layer. Garnish top with green pepper rings. Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: chocolate fudge sundae layer bars
directions: Combine flour, oleo and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together; add Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture over crust. Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese.
Top with more Cool Whip.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix with mixer until it looks like pie dough before water is added.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jiffy chow mein
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add onion, celery and 1 cup water. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add bean sprouts.
Combine soy sauce, sugar, water and cornstarch and add to meat.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Serve over Chinese noodles or rice, if desired.
Serves 6 amply.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 3 hours before serving.
Serve with raw cauliflower, celery, carrots, broccoli and green peppers.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up and wrap in Saran Wrap (jelly roll fashion).
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into pieces.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: grandmother's fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine margarine, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Continue for 5 minutes over medium heat and stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place into greased shallow pan.
Put in fridge until firm (about 20 minutes) and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine margarine and water; add oats.
Allow to stand 30 minutes.
Add eggs, sugar and brown sugar; mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Bake in a 12 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes (grease and flour pan).

title: torta mexican-style
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to package directions.
While bread is rising, prepare ground beef with taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Squeeze excess moisture from spinach and combine with cheese.
Salt to taste.
When fillings are prepared, divide dough into 3 portions and roll each into a 9-inch round.
Fit one portion into a buttered 9-inch spring-form pan. Spread meat almost to edges of dough.
Add next layer of dough and top with spinach mixture.
Place last portion of dough on top and cover with damp cloth.
Set Torta in warm place to rise about 40 minutes.
When it is about double in size, score top with a sharp knife into 8 pie-shaped wedges.
Brush top with egg.
Bake on lower rack in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until bread is deep, gold brown.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter oblong baking dish; lay bread slices in dish.
Tear chicken into pieces and lay on top bread.
Put the mushrooms over chicken.
Mix the soups and mayonnaise; pour over chicken.
Add the pimento.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top (as much as you like).
In a small bowl mix eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over top. Take a knife and cut through criss-cross.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keep covered and bake at 350 degrees for one hour. Mix the herb dressing mix and butter and sprinkle over top.
Keep covered and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: lemon cake
directions: Cook as directed on cake mix box in a rectangular pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese 15 seconds in microwave.
Mix cheese well with mayo, onions, garlic and salt.
Stir in shrimp.
Chill at least 30 minutes.

title: mushroom crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown mushrooms in margarine; stir in salt, onion, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until liquid evaporates.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut and squeeze orange; add to 1/2 cup sugar and set aside.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix sour cream, oranges and pineapple well.
Add marshmallows, coconut and pecans.
Stir well, then refrigerate. This salad is better if made the day before you serve it.

title: caesar salad
directions: Cut lettuce, tomatoes, green onions and cucumber into bowl. Dice Feta cheese and put on top.
Add the olives and vegita on top.
Squeeze lemon on top.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, peas, soup and noodles in casserole, Top with crumbs (chips, crackers or cereal).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef, season to taste.
Drain fat.
Follow directions on back of enchilada sauce mix.
Lightly grease dish. On flour shell spread 1 tablespoon of refried beans and spread 1 tablespoon sour cream.
Top with cheese, add ground beef, then roll tightly as possible.
Then pour sauce mix over all and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Mix and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Save 1/2 cup of mixture for top.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornmeal, butter and vanilla.
Stir in eggs; mix thoroughly.
Pour in unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Requires no eggs.
Sometimes I add one.

title: salsa
directions: In a medium size bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover; let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Salsa will get hotter the longer it stands.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well in a large bowl.
Keep chilled.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together with mayonnaise or sour cream.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on salad greens.
Garnish with grated cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; blend in the rest of ingredients.
Bake in 4 greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split cake(very sinful but delicious)
directions: Pat graham crackers and oleo into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 15 minutes (no less), oleo, confectioners sugar and eggs.
Spread over crumbs.
Add drained pineapple over 2nd layer, cover with sliced bananas and large container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with walnuts or pecans and cherries and let stand overnight.

title: summer surprise dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine all fruit together; mix well. Sprinkle brown sugar over the fruit.
Top with sour cream.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat eggs and brown sugar until smooth.
Add milk, flour, salt, baking powder, soda and banana; mix.
Add nuts.
Bake in waxed paper lined pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes two loaves.

title: s&w lasagna ole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; spread 1/3 of mixture in bottom of 7 x 11-inch microwave baking dish.
Layer 2 corn tortillas on top. Combine next 4 ingredients with 1/2 cup of each shredded cheese; spoon 1/2 mixture over tortillas.
Repeat layers, ending with salsa mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes, rotating dish during cooking.
Remove wrap; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand until cheese melts; cut into squares.
Serves 6.

title: creamy cabbage coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Combine and mix the sugar, salt, celery seed, vinegar, mayonnaise and salad oil.
Mix cabbage into dressing. Refrigerate until cold.

title: wild rice and chicken salad
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Add celery and onions the last 5 minutes.
Add dressing to coat.
Chill.
Before serving, add fruit, nuts and meat.
If desired, add a little more dressing. Can also be served warm.

title: montez's rolls
directions: Combine yeast after dissolved in 1/2 cup of warm water, Crisco oil, eggs and buttermilk, then mix dry ingredients with liquid ingredients.
Beat with mixer or knead until smooth.
Put into large bowl and cover so it can rise.
Always make dough up the night before and put into icebox.
Be sure when dough begins to rise.
Shake it back down.
This will make rolls or cinnamon rolls.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Combine turkey, crumbs, milk, onion, egg, bouillon, 1 teaspoon mustard and poultry seasoning.
Mix well.
In shallow baking dish, shape into loaf. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Combine remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons mustard, honey and brown sugar. Spoon over loaf.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until no longer pink.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook until syrup turns dark, hard crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Add last 3 ingredients. Pour into well buttered pan.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine punch and frozen concentrates with water.
Pour over ice ring in large punch bowl.
Carefully add ginger ale.

title: pizza style lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Lay noodles out on wax paper or towel.
Lay layer of noodles in pan.
Pour sauce over noodles until covered.
Put sausage, pepperoni and then cheese.
Put another layer of noodles on top and do the same again.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked lemon pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops with flour, pepper and salt.
Brown in a little hot fat on both sides.
(Drain off excess fat after browning.)
Put a 1/2 slice of lemon on each chop.
Mix ketchup, water and brown sugar; pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until done, time depending on thickness of the chops.
You might have to add a little water in latter part of baking if sauce cooks down too much.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken in flour mixture.
Heat oven to 350°.
Put butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and melt.
Put floured chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Mix together the pineapple juice, brown sugar, onion, thyme and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Turn chicken when done baking; pour mixture over the chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes; garnish with pineapple slices the last 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, flour, soda a little salt and vanilla together. Add other ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a large tube pan.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Place meat and onions in frying pan to brown.
While meat is browning, combine the rest of the ingredients (except the chow mein noodles) in a large bowl and mix well.
When meat is done, drain whatever grease may accumulate and add the meat and onions to the mixture.
Mix well.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a heavy cooking pan or double boiler, combine milk, evaporated milk, vanilla and butter. In a mixing bowl, mix together sugar, flour and cocoa. Divide eggs; set aside whites. Beat yolks and stir into liquid in cooking pan. Heat on medium and gradually stir in the dry mixture. Continue to stir well. When mixture thickens, remove from heat and beat until smooth. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Add green onions, green peppers and sliced olives to cooled rice.
Cut up drained artichokes and add to rice.
Combine marinade with curry powder and mayonnaise.
Add to rice and toss. Chill.
You can also add chicken, water chestnuts or almonds.

title: baked fruit
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle fruit with almonds.
Combine butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; top the fruit with mixture.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple crunch(large quantity recipe)
directions: In pot, combine apples, water, 1 c. (2 sticks) margarine, and sugar; season with apple pie spice to taste. Cook till hot and flavors are blended.; remove from heat and thicken with a little cornstarch and water.

title: zucchini preserves
directions: Cook zucchini and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Cook 6 minutes more.
Add apricot jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir all together.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Mix in bowl the cooked carrots and pepper.
In saucepan, mix soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Bring to a boil and stir until well mixed.
Pour over carrots mix. Chill overnight or several hours.
Keeps in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix Accent, Lawry's seasoned salt, lemon juice and oil.
Add mayonnaise.
Add cooked noodles and other ingredients.

title: lorine little's rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt in a small mixing
bowl.
Stir
until
shortening
and
sugar
are dissolved. Cool.
Add
beaten
eggs.
Meanwhile,
in
a large bowl,
let yeast
mixed
with lukewarm water stand 5 minutes, then
stir
and pour
first
mixture into the large bowl with yeast.
Add
4 cups
of
flour and beat well with an electric mixer.
Add
the remaining
2 1/2 cups flour and mix by hand. Cover and place in refrigerator at least 4 hours.
(Dough will keep for
days.) Shape rolls and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue catfish(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl.
Arrange fillets in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish that has been coated with cooking spray.
Pour catsup mixture over fillets; cover and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes, turning once.
Remove fillets from marinade, reserving marinade.
Bring marinade to a boil in a small saucepan; boil 2 minutes.
Place fillets on rack of a broiler pan that has been coated with cooking spray.
Broil 6 inches from heat 14 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, basting occasionally with marinade.
Transfer to a serving platter.
Yield:
6 servings (156 calories per serving).
Fat: 6.4 grams per serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (drain grease).
Add tomato soup, 1/4 cup ketchup and 2 squirts mustard.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Soak Doritos in chicken broth.
Line greased casserole dish. Place chicken pieces in dish. Sprinkle onion, pepper and half of the cheese.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Mix soups together and add. Put tomatoes on top and cook 35 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven and add remainder of cheese. Cut oven off and let set for 10 minutes.

title: turkey patties
directions: Measure 3/4 cup of the stuffing crumbs; crush and set aside. Combine contents of vegetable seasoning packet, water and half the condensed soup in medium saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup butter and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 6 minutes.
Add remaining stuffing crumbs and stir just to moisten.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix in egg and turkey and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 8 patties and roll in crushed crumbs.
Brown on all sides in skillet in 2 tablespoons butter. Add milk to remaining condensed soup; heat and serve over patties. Makes 4 servings.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash; add sour cream, chicken soup, carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a layer of crumbs in a shallow greased casserole dish (12 x 7-inch).
Spoon squash mixture over crumbs. Cover squash mixture with additional crumbs on top and then dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fish bake
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan. Cook spinach as directed on package. Drain well. Squeeze dry. Saute onion in oil until transparent; add spinach and cook 2 or 3 minutes. Spread in prepared pan. Wipe fish fillets with damp paper towel.
Mix dill weed with sour cream and spread on both sides of fish.
Place on top of spinach in pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450° or until fish flakes easily. Dot with butter.
Place under broiler until lightly browned.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix eggs and milk together.
Stir in sugar, flour and nutmeg. Mix in rhubarb.
Put in pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter (optional).
Cover with top crust, if desired.
Bake at 400° for about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: bean and bacon loaf
directions: Soak beans overnight; cook until tender, about 45 minutes. Cook bacon.
Run beans, bread, celery and bacon through the food chopper.
Blend with egg and peanut butter; add the fat remaining from the crisped bacon.
Mold into loaf and bake in slow oven about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 and is delicious with tomato sauce. The remaining can be sliced and served cold the following day.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased casserole dish until it bubbles at 350°.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Chop beef into small pieces.
In a large pot, boil beef for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, tomatoes (chopped with juice) and vegetables to pot.
Cook 1 hour.
Add pasta, salt and pepper. Cook another 30 minutes.

title: ray hutchison's homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: These ingredients are for a 1 gallon freezer; multiply or reduce proportionately for 1/2 or 1 1/2 gallon freezers.

title: peanut butter brownie pie(microwave)
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Cut peanut butter cups into quarters.
In a medium bowl, melt chocolate pieces and margarine on High, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and baking powder, then peanut butter cup quarters.
Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle peanuts in ring 1 inch from edge of plate.
On microwave cooking rack, cook on Medium (50% power) 8 minutes, rotating dish halfway through cooking.
Rotate dish; cook on High 2 to 3 minutes, until toothpick inserted 2 inches from edge comes out clean.
Let stand on countertop covered with wax paper until cool.
Makes 10 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
When cold, peel and grate.
In medium pan, combine butter, sour cream, cheese and salt.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Add onions and pour over potatoes which have been placed in a buttered baking dish. Sprinkle top with paprika and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: southern fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs together. Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: summer spread
directions: On flat large plate, spread cream cheese.
Cover with cocktail sauce and rest of ingredients.
Serve with heavy crackers.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with crackers.
Mix pudding and milk. Add sour cream.
Mix well and add whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 of pudding over crackers.
Place on this another layer of crackers. Spread other half of pudding over these and put third layer of crackers on top.
Spread frosting over last layer of crackers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar; continue to beat mixture.
Add vanilla.
Alternate with eggs and flour until all is mixed.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 1 1/2 hours until toothpick comes out clean.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Drop cleaned frozen shrimp into boiling water; return to a rolling boil and boil shrimp for approximately 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain shrimp in colander.
Rinse in cold water and set aside.
Mix tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, garlic powder, salt, pepper, barbecue sauce and Worcestershire sauce in large pan, preferably an iron skillet.
Add shrimp to hot mixture.
Stir well. Simmer for 5 minutes.
(If sauce is thinner than you like, add mixture of 1 teaspoon corn starch in 1/2 cup water.)
Serve over cooked rice.

title: boushalla--persian soup
directions: Note:
This extremely popular recipe takes some time to prepare, but is worth it.
The recipe features oversized, infused croutons and a full-flavored fusion dressing with strong balsamic signatures and herbs de Provence.

title: savory spaghetti squash(low-fat main dish-heart healthy)
directions: Cook squash 30 minutes in rapidly boiling water.
Cool.
Cut in half; remove seeds and scrape out pulp, using edge of spoon. Melt butter over medium heat.
Saute squash for 3 minutes, stirring to avoid browning.
Set aside.
Slice pepper into very thin strips.
Slice carrots julienne style.
Pour oil onto peppers and carrots, using just enough to coat lightly.
Stir-fry briefly until barely tender.
Add mushrooms, pineapple and squash.
Toss until well mixed.
Add soy sauce, stirring constantly.
Fold in chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat just long enough to heat through.
Serve immediately over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add pineapple to sugar and bring to boil.
Add gelatin.
Stir until gelatin dissolves.
Then add juices and let cool.
Mash cream cheese and cherries.
Combine with pineapple mixture, adding a small amount at a time.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip cream and blend into salad.

title: berry pie
directions: Line a pie plate with pastry and fill with berries. Dredge with flour, salt and sugar which have been mixed together.
Dot with small piece of butter.
Cover with top crust or strips of pastry across top.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush crackers to make crust in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Add 1/2 cup melted butter to crackers.
Top with boiled chicken. Mix soups and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Top with crushed crackers and remaining butter.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: layered cranberry cheddar spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer relish, Cheddar cheese and cream cheese mixture in a 1 1/2-quart clear glass container.
Garnish with additional Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Serve with crackers or fruit wedges.

title: french pork pies
directions: Cook pork, salt, pepper, onions and sage on medium heat, stirring to break up meat.
Simmer for approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Skim off fat.
Add seasoning if necessary.
Cook potatoes; mash, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Mix potatoes and pork, stirring to blend.
Fill pastry shells.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.
Cool completely before refrigerating or freezing.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with sliced fresh fruit.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Peel and grate sweet potatoes and mix with other ingredients. Pour into well-greased pie plate.
Drizzle top with melted butter. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until set.

title: moist oatmeal cake
directions: Mix and spread on cake after it is baked.
Return to oven until topping bubbles.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Boil zucchini until clear.
Add pineapple and mix good.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add sugar, Sure-Jell and jello.
Boil hard for 6 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Boil 2 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.
Keep in refrigerator or freeze.

title: banana nut crunch bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat eggs; stir in bananas, oil and water.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened. Stir in cereal; pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Makes 18 (1/2-inch) slices.

title: norma's bread
directions: Melt margarine and pour into tube cake pan.
Rotate pan to cover sides with margarine.
Place biscuits, standing on sides, in pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Invert onto plate and separate biscuits when cool enough to handle.

title: baked apples
directions: Roll apple halves lightly in flour and place in a buttered baking pan, side up from which core was removed.
Sprinkle with sugars and cinnamon.
Repeat sprinkling in that order about 3 times until you have a sufficient amount of sugar and cinnamon.
Dot each piece of apple with butter and nuts.
Drizzle with light cream or milk.
Bake until tender at 350°.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine the sugar, margarine and milk; bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly (mixture scorches easily).
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Place in order in large bowl.
Let sit for 24 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, toss and mix.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Put in a greased baking dish and top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: linda's chicken
directions: Saute chicken breasts that have been dipped into egg and bread crumbs in butter.
Place in casserole dish that has 1/2 cup melted butter in it.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon garlic onto chicken. Saute sliced mushrooms and pour over chicken.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, Crisco and add 1 egg; beat and add cake flour. Blend; add 2 eggs and beat in.
Add 1 more cup flour; blend.
Add eggs and blend.
Add sour cream and beat.
Add flavorings.
Beat well.
Grease Bundt pan and flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar on top.
Put foil around sides of pan.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package.
Add juices, using only half as much water in lemonade as directed on can.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips. Bake in tube pan on 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix broccoli, eggs, cottage cheese, butter and onion. Add corn muffin mix and salt; bake in hot greased skillet at 375° until shiny on top, about 45 minutes.

title: my low-fat biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil and milk; mix until flour is moistened.
Roll out on lightly floured board; cut with cutter.
Place in ungreased pan; bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add Eagle Brand milk; beat.
Add Pet milk and vanilla; beat.
Pour into ice cream container.
Finish filling with homogenized milk.

title: braised beef
directions: Flour and brown beef in frying pan.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Put meat in oblong baking dish.
Add tomatoes.
Dice onion, celery and pepper; add to other ingredients.
Add spices to taste. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Great with ham!

title: oven omelet brunch(a memorial day tradition)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In oven, melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Coat bottom with butter.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt until blended.
Stir in onion.
Bake until eggs are set, approximately 35 minutes.

title: cake icing
directions: Blend.
Add color if you want to and then spread on cake.

title: "do-ahead" fruit salad
directions: Melt marshmallows with 3 tablespoons strawberry juice; stir and cool.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Blend Miracle Whip with cream cheese, then blend into marshmallow mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook corn, potatoes, celery, onion, salt and pepper in 1 cup water until tender. Stir in soup, milk and crackers. Heat just to boiling. Serve hot in soup bowls. Sprinkle with bacon garnish.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use 3 teaspoons of mix for 1 cup.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda and baking powder; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients, Rice Krispies, oatmeal and coconut.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: velvet cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar gradually, yolk of eggs well beaten and water.
Mix and sift flour, cornstarch and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Then add whites of eggs beaten until stiff.
After putting in pan, cover with almonds and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake forty minutes in a moderate oven.

title: creamy strawberry punch
directions: Place thawed strawberries in blender container.
Process until pureed.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and sherbet.
Stir until creamy.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Take pork chops, roll in seasoned flour and brown on both sides in hot frypan with oil.
While chops are browning, take soup and milk and mix together to make sauce.
Put potatoes in baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Put pork chops on top of potatoes and pour soup over evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Make a biscuit dough using Bisquick and water; roll into a rectangular shape about 1/4 inch thick.
Cover with uncooked sausage.
Carefully roll up and slice into 1/2 or 3/4-inch slices. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 5.
These can be made ahead and frozen.
Reheat in microwave oven.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; spread on top of cooled crust.
Refrigerate.

title: hu nang shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp.
Add wine, water, cornstarch and salt.
Mix with shrimp.
Chop onion.
Turn to high heat.
Heat vegetable oil and add shrimp.
Saute until shrimp changes color.
Check both sides of shrimp (about 3 minutes).
Remove shrimp.
Saute onions 1 minute.
Add shrimp, sugar and the tomato sauce.
Remove and stir 1 minute.
Serve.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash until just tender and drain. Combine with sour cream, soup, onion and water chestnuts. Top with stuffing mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over hot water. Combine the remaining ingredients.
Add gelatin and blend.
Pour into a 1 quart mold (which has been rinsed in cold water).
Chill until firm.
Serve with caper sauce if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and make into a ball. Roll ball in chopped nuts.

title: apricot balls
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: cabbage roll
directions: Roll meat mixture in cabbage leaves and fasten with a toothpick.
Brown in butter and place in a casserole to bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: super spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat fat in large skillet.
Add hamburger and brown well. Push meat to the side of the pan, add onions, green peppers and garlic.
Cook until onions are clear.
Add tomatoes, sauce and seasonings; mix well.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer the first 7 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles and cool.
Line greased 9 x 13-inch pan with one layer of noodles, 1/2 of sauce, layer of cottage cheese, more noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with Mozzarella (shredded).
Bake for 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: chunky milk chocolate cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.

In a larger bowl, cream the sugar, butter and vanilla. Beat in egg. Add dry ingredients; beat well. Stir in morsels, nuts and raisins.
