Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Flatten slightly. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken broth 10 minutes; add remaining ingredients except cheese, mixing well.
Place in large flat baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Serves 12 or more. Freezes well.
Leftover turkey can be used.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain shrimp into sieve and wash. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well with mixer and chill well. When ready to serve, mix again and pat into serving dish.

title: boggs' italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry. Place in shallow baking pan.
In saucepan, melt butter; add dressing mix and dry mustard.
Baste pieces with mixture.
Bake for 1 hour, basting often.

title: low-fat banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil, applesauce and sugar together.
Add eggs and bananas; beat well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt to first mixture with milk and vanilla.
Beat well and stir in nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 large loaves.

title: spiced tea
directions: Use 2 teaspoons per cup.
Serve hot.

title: 7-up barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Place meat in sauce and bake slowly or baste meat frequently as it cooks.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix the 4 beaten eggs, salad oil, sugar and pumpkin together. Add the flour, soda, cloves, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour into greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix packaged corn bread per directions on back of box.
Add corn, small amount of cheese and ground beef.
Pour 1/2 mixture in pan and add a layer of shredded cheese.
Pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake in oven as package directs.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in a large heavy kettle; drain fat.
Add all the ingredients except cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
If you prefer thinner soup, add additional water or broth.
Yield:
12 servings.
Diabetic exchange:
one serving equals 1 protein, 1 bread, 152 calories, 776 mg. sodium and 4 grams fat.

title: lans potato chicken
directions: Cover with water and boil 1 hour and 15 minutes until done. No set amount of chicken or vegetables.
Use amount you like.

directions: Pour boiling hot

Sift all dry ingredients.
Add egg to date mixture and blend well.

Serve with softened cream cheese.

title: fried potato patties
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Shape mixture into 6 patties. Dip each patty into lightly beaten egg and lightly coat with bread crumbs.
Pour vegetable oil into a large skillet.
Fry in hot oil over medium heat until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cheesy mixed vegetable bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease a large casserole dish. Combine vegetables, half of pimento, soup, sour cream, pepper, half of fried onions, and half of the cheese into a bowl and mix. Spoon mixture into prepared casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining fried onions and cheese on top of casserole.
Bake additional 5 minutes.
Remove casserole from oven and sprinkle with remaining pimento.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and egg, then beat.
Then add dry ingredients (sifted); add mashed bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in large loaf pan, greased and floured.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, sugar and salt in large bowl. With 2 knives or pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese, onion and dill.
Mix well.
Combine milk and beaten egg; pour into flour mixture all at once. Stir quickly with fork just to moisten flour mixture.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix salmon, eggs and onion together.
Add soup and milk to salmon.
Add noodles.
Pour into casserole dish.
Brush margarine on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chinese beef and rice
directions: Cook rice in oil over medium-high heat until golden brown, stirring constantly so as not to burn.
Add salt, water, bouillon cube and soy sauce.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: apple pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1/2 cup muffin pans.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine sugar, oil, egg, lemon juice, vanilla and lemon peel.
Whisk to blend.
Mix in dry ingredients, then apples and pecans.
Spoon 1/3 cup batter into each muffin cup.
Bake about 35 minutes.
Turn muffins out on rack.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm.
Yields 12.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Clean and remove centers of bell peppers.
It helps to punch a few holes on bottoms of bell peppers to let excess grease drain. Mix all other ingredients and stuff bell peppers.
Use 1/2 can tomato sauce to cover tops of bell peppers.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mildred's sausage and bean chowder
directions: Brown sausage in heavy pan; drain off grease.
Combine all ingredients and seasoning but corn and sugar.
Simmer approximately 1 hour.
Add corn and sugar last 5 minutes just to heat.

title: venison salad
directions: Marinate cubed venison in French dressing for 1 hour in the refrigerator, stirring occasionally.
When ready to serve, drain excess dressing from meat.
Combine with all remaining ingredients, saving a few olives and egg slices for garnish. Season to taste.
Arrange in salad bowl edged with salad greens. Garnish with reserved olive slices, egg slices and pickles.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; cream shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add eggs one at a time.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Make small balls; roll in white sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes.
They will flatten and crack like boughten gingersnaps.
Let rest on cookie sheet a few minutes after removing from oven.
Place on rack or pan to cool.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Place pork chops in 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Mix soup and water thoroughly and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: grilled bananas
directions: Heat grill.
Place bananas on gas grill over medium heat or on charcoal grill 4 to 6 inches from medium coals.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until peels are brown and bananas are soft, turning once.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, milk and sugar.
Pour into pan.
Put in peaches and pat butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons butter and the oil in Dutch oven. Brown chicken on all sides.
Pour on boiling water to cover chicken. Add onion, celery, carrot and bay leaf. Cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes. Strain broth and reduce to 1 1/2 cups.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter. Stir in flour and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Slowly add cream and broth. Stir and simmer 4 to 5 minutes until smooth and thick. Add lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Add strawberries (with liquid), eggs, oil and pecans and mix just enough to blend in.
Pour into two large, greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, or until golden brown.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.
Makes two loaves.

title: aunt jan's meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Blot and drain meatballs.

title: barbados beef stew
directions: Sprinkle beef with flour and brown in oil.
Add tomatoes, onion, celery salt, salt and pepper.
Combine vinegar, molasses and water and add to meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender. Add carrots, raisins and ginger.
Cook until carrots are tender. Good with rice or noodles.

title: broccoli-rice quiche
directions: Cook onions with broccoli.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine rice, 3/4 cup cheese, 2 eggs (slightly beaten) and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Press firmly and evenly over bottom and sides of 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.

title: holly candy(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Melt marshmallows in butter in top of double boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Add vanilla and coloring.
Add corn flakes.
Stir until completely covered with green mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
While still warm, decorate with red hots.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian sausage salad
directions: Cook sausages, first prick skins with a fork, put them in a skillet with water to cover, bring to a boil, reduce heat and poach for 1 minute.
Drain off the water, slice sausage into bite-size pieces and fry over medium heat in a dry skillet until browned through.
Cook and drain the macaroni.

title: chocomint float
directions: Fill mug halfway full with hot chocolate.
Add 1 scoop of peppermint ice cream.
Top it with holiday candy.
Then add a swirl of whipped cream and 2 peppermint sticks for added flavor.

title: north pole chowder
directions: Cook broccoli in cheese sauce according to package directions, only until thawed.
Place broccoli in cheese sauce in blender and grate; blend until finely chopped.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add seasonings, bouillon and grated broccoli.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: corn chowder soup
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine soup, corn, milk, green peppers, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Microwave at High 17 to 19 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Add chives and serve.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: If using fresh sweet potatoes, place in a kettle, cover with water and cook, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or just until tender. Drain; cool slightly. Peel and cut into chunks. Place cooked or canned sweet potato chunks in 2-quart baking dish. In small saucepan, combine butter, syrup, brown sugar and cinnamon; cook and stir until mixture boils. Pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through. Yields 8 servings.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Take out 1 cup for topping. Mix 1 cup brown sugar and boiling water.
Add baking soda in boiling water.
Add this to crumb mixture and beat well.
Pour into cupcake papers 2/3 full and add crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix powdered pudding with Cool Whip, fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Place in serving dish.
Top with fruit of your choice and chill in the refrigerator for 4 hours.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Just mix and you're set to go.

title: nellie's spinach dip
directions: Soften cream cheese for 30 seconds in the microwave oven. Blend together all ingredients with a fork.
Chill for at least one hour.
Good dip for any vegetable.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients except the bacon in a casserole.
Mix well.
Put the diced bacon on top (unfried) so bacon juices flow through the beans while baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes covered and then for 15 minutes uncovered.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding onions last.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Brush on steak, chicken, ribs or chops.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Soak 1 cup of Grape-Nuts cereal in 2 cups sour milk or buttermilk for 1 hour.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake in greased and floured bread pans at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tom and jerry batter
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites with salt and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add 1/2 pound of the sugar.
Beat egg yolks and baking powder.
Then gradually add the other 1/2 of baking powder.
Last, mix whites and yolk mixes all together.
Add nutmeg to taste.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt marshmallows and caramel nuggets in double boiler, then add peanut butter.
When all is melted, take from fire and add noodles.
Mix until noodles are covered, then drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Let cream come to room temperature.
Cook fettuccine noodles and drain.
Add all ingredients; mix until the noodles are covered with sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add corn, milk, oil and salt; mix well. Fold in muffin mix and pour into an 8 x 8-inch dish that has been lightly greased.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with 1 cup crushed cornflakes and up to 1 stick melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook each vegetable according to directions on package.
Melt Crisco in saucepan, stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Stir in half and half and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Blend in Tabasco, mustard and horseradish.
Cook 1 minute.
Drain cooked vegetables and shredded cheese.
Fold into cream sauce.
Pour into a 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or cheese is melted.

title: banana bread(fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With electric mixer, blend water and honey.
Beat in egg.
Add banana; blend in.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture; stir in walnuts. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: marbled pumpkin cream pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Slowly stir in milk and cook.
Stir constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Remove 1 cup of the mixture and place it into another saucepan.
Place 2 egg yolks into each of 2 small bowls.
Beat lightly.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: spiced apple juice warm-up
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling point.
Remove cinnamon.
Pour into thermos to keep hot until needed.

title: health bread
directions: Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar, milk, egg, salt and soda.
Add raisins.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.

title: mama walker's chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in water and remove from bone.
Saute mushrooms in 1 1/2 tablespoons butter and set aside.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan (lightly greased, pay close attention to corners and edges) with cut up chicken.
Mix remainder of chicken, broth and soups together (heat slightly to even out soups).
Pour over chicken. Add sauteed mushrooms.
Mix flour, milk and melted butter.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In a heavy bottom saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, egg and juice from pineapple.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Cool; stir in Cool Whip.
In a large bowl, mix apples, pineapple chunks, marshmallows and peanuts.
Toss with the dressing.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Sift half the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to milk and egg mixture.
Beat batter with mixer, adding only as much flour as needed to leave batter thin enough to run through funnel.
Heat vegetable oil to about 375° in 8-inch or 9-inch iron skillet, about 3/4 inch deep.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter into funnel, keeping finger over bottom of funnel until ready to drizzle batter in hot oil.
Swirl and crisscross batter in oil to make a lace like pattern.
Let cake brown on one side, turn and brown other side (the whole process takes less than one minute).
Remove and place on plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar, syrup, molasses, jelly or cherry pie filling.
Serve immediately.

title: tomato grits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease shallow 2-quart baking dish.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, onion soup, stuffing mix and salt. Divide into thirds.
Form each into a loaf.
Place loaves into a 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1-1/2 hours.
In a medium bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Set aside.
Drain juices off meat loaves and top with brown sugar mixture.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: curried scallops
directions: Coat a medium nonstick skillet with vegetable oil.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add next 3 ingredients; saute 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat and set aside. Keep warm.

title: kathy's graham cracker treats
directions: Arrange Graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Bring sugar, butter and margarine to a boil for exactly 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle pecans over crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for exactly 10 minutes.
Let set for one minute. Remove crackers from cookie sheet onto wax paper.
Cool and enjoy.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Thaw frozen broccoli or spinach and drain off as much liquid as possible.
Mix the broccoli (spinach) together with the rest of the ingredients and chill for one hour.
Serve with chips, vegetables or crackers.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Cook asparagus.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over hot asparagus and chill.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add egg, beaten with some of the flour, then add buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle on top the following (mixed together): 1 cup white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: betty rose's chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and 1/4 cup milk in saucepan.
Heat to boiling and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Mix in 1/4 stick butter and set aside to cool.

title: apple goodie
directions: Put sliced apples in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar, egg and butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Mix other ingredients and pour over butter. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to dry mixture.
Use right amount of milk to make right consistency batter.
Fry in deep hot fat (365° to 375°) until done, which will take about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fabulous spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop all ingredients as fine as possible.
Cook meat in olive oil and butter until done, not browned.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: newfoundland lobster salad
directions: Cut lobster into bite-size pieces and toss with ingredients. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: maxine's peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, peanuts and water in a heavy saucepan, stirring constantly.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add oleo, vanilla and food coloring.
Continue to stir and beat intermittingly until it begins to lose a glossy color.
Then pour into greased cookie sheet or make foil molds the size of patties you want.
Cool and eat.
(Very good.)

title: mashed turnips
directions: Wash turnips and peel; slice thinly across grain to break vertical fibers.
Place in kettle with 1/2 cup water and simmer, covered, until tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove cover for last few minutes to cook away excess water.
Add butter and sprinklings of salt and pepper and mash turnips.
Return to burner to heat through.
Serve hot.

title: pasta amatriciana
directions: In a large frying pan or medium saucepan, fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Set aside.
Drain pan of all but 2 to 3 tablespoons fat.
Add onions and garlic and saute until translucent.
Chop tomatoes to a coarse texture and add to pan. Simmer on high.
Stir often, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add crumbled bacon, oregano, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serve immediately over favorite pasta.
Garnish with fresh grated Parmesan or Romano.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef. Saut onions in oil. Put beef and onions in a large Dutch oven. Add all remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven or microwave until tender (1 hour in oven or 12 to 16 minutes in microwave).
Slice in half lengthwise and scoop potato from shells, reserving shells.
Combine potato with remaining ingredients and replace mixture into shells.
Place in Pyrex dish and heat until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: english trifle
directions: Cover the bottom of a large glass bowl with
a double layer of sliced jelly roll.
Pour sherry over the jelly roll, then place the sliced peaches on top of it. (Do not use the juice from the peaches or the jelly roll will be soggy.)
Make jello and when it's cool, pour on top of peaches.
When the jello is set, make the pudding and when cool, pour on top of the jello.
When this is set, beat the whipping cream until it stands in peaks.
Add a few drops of vanilla to the whipping cream.
Pour on top of pudding and then decorate the cream with the cherries and sliced almonds. (Fresh strawberries can be used instead of cherries when in season.)

title: sue's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix together soup and sour cream in bowl.
Make stuffing according to directions on box.
Put chicken on bottom of baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Add stuffing on top and bake at 350° for about one-half hour or until stuffing is brown and crunchy.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until smooth.
Cook on lightly greased griddle or heavy skillet.

title: salmon noodle bake
directions: Flake salmon and add salmon liquid; add to remaining ingredients and toss them.
Add dry bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in thawed non-dairy whipped topping, blending thoroughly. Spoon into crust. Chill until set, about 4 hours. Serve topped with cherry pie filling if desired.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and drain spinach thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: corn and sausage chowder
directions: Heat all ingredients, stirring frequently.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion, parsley, eggs, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and 1/2 jar of sauce.
Divide into 3 parts.
Put 1 part in bottom of loaf pan; sprinkle with half of cheese.
Repeat meat, cheese, then rest of meat.
Pour remaining sauce over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cajun stew
directions: Make a roux (dark, thick gravy).
Add broth from roast and water until a thin gravy.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until potatoes are done.
Server over rice.

title: big country biscuit wraps
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Press each biscuit into 5 inch round. Spoon ham and cheese onto center of each biscuit.
Fold dough in half over filling, press edges with fork to seal.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pizzelle
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Melt butter.
Add flavoring.
Cool, then add to egg mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add and mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on greased (first one) pizzelle iron.
Cook until golden.

title: cassava bibingka
directions: Mix well and bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cut all ingredients together with two knives or pastry cutter to make dough; keeping as dry as possible.
Roll out into a square.
Cut in strips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes until light brown and crisp.
Let cool.

title: texas omelette
directions: Layer croutons in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dice sausage links and saute them with the onions and green peppers.
Sprinkle the sausage, onions and green peppers over the croutons.
Beat the eggs and add the Worcestershire sauce, soup and milk.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Layer the shredded cheese over the sausage and vegetables.
Pour the egg mixture into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: potato tortillas
directions: Peel potatoes and boil in salted water until very tender; drain and mash.
Add butter and chopped onions.
Form little potato ball with Mozzarella cheese in the center.
After placing cheese in the center, flatten the potato/cheese ball to form a flat "tortilla."
Fry until golden.
Goes great with any kind of steak or chicken.
Serves 6.

title: lipton vegie chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: berry pirovette torte
directions: Prepare gelatin by pouring boiling water on gelatin in large bowl; stir until completely dissolved.
Place all but 4 to 5 berries into food processor or blender and process until smooth. Stir berries into gelatin.
Refrigerate about 1 hour, until very thick but not set.

title: smashed tators
directions: Have mom peel and boil potatoes.
Drain water.
Add milk. Mash.
Add butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Eat up! Yum! Yum!

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot cooker.
Cook on low 6 to 10 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours.

title: skier's stew from pico, vt
directions: Cook, covered, at 325° for at least 3 hours.
If cooking for 5 hours, lower temperature slightly.
If using a crock-pot, cook on low setting for 10 to 12 hours or on high setting for 5 to 6 hours.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Make into 4 or 5 rolls and roll in chili powder and paprika mix.
Wrap in wax paper or foil and chill.
Will keep about 3 months in refrigerator.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the 2 cups of
sugar and the shortening.	Add the eggs and beat.
Sift flour,
cup cocoa and salt together. Add to mixture.
Add 3
teaspoons	vanilla
and
1 cup chopped nuts. Pour into a greased
and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45
minutes.

title: nancy's apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift	dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Fold in sliced
apples
and
chopped
nuts. Bake in	angel
food cake pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start mixture in a cold oven.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in bite size pieces and set aside.
Heat oil in a heavy boiler until hot.
Add cabbage, salt and black pepper.
Add water.
Place lid on boiler and cook on high about 5 minutes. Reduce heat to medium and cook until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes total time.
Don't overcook.

title: fresh garden corn
directions: Cut kernels from fresh corn to measure 2 cups.
Stir all ingredients together in microwave-safe bowl and microwave, covered, for 5 minutes.
Great stuff.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions on package. Brown ground beef and drain; add tomato sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan put a layer of sauce, then layer of noodles, then half of the cottage cheese and layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat, ending with sauce on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add celery and onion; cook about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add chicken, almonds and mushrooms; toss to coat well. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips. Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: arroz con pollo (chicken with rice)
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt.
In 12 inch skillet brown chicken in hot oil about 15 minutes until brown.
Remove chicken from pan. In drippings remaining in pain, cook rice, onion and garlic till rice is golden.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, red pepper, bouillon granules, salt and pepper; bring to boiling, stir gently.
Arrange chicken atop rice mixture; cover and simmer 30 - 35 minutes or till chicken is tender.
Makes 4 - 6 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, margarine and syrup with hand beater. Stir in pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until set, about 50 minutes. Cool slightly.
Serve warm or refrigerate.

title: fruit punch slush
directions: Combine bananas and frozen fruit juices in blender; blend until smooth.
Combine banana mixture, pineapple juice, water and sugar in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour into plastic freezer containers or molds and freeze.
To serve, thaw until mushy and add carbonated beverage.
Garnish with orange slices.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: wonderful corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese on stove top.
Stir in corn and green chilies.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until firm and light brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in buttered baking dish. Top with crushed cornflakes (can use Product 19 or Total cereal). Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple goody dessert
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon, white sugar, flour and 1/2 cup broken nutmeats together and place in casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients together in mixing bowl and spread over apple mixture. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; cream butter. Add sugar and cream well. Add eggs and beat. Add flour, mixing well. Add vanilla and coconut. Chill dough until firm enough to roll. Roll dough 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured board. Cut with floured 3-inch cutter and sprinkle with sugar. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 12 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: carrot pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, beaten eggs, milk, salt, carrots, vanilla and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust. Bake for 45 minutes or until firm in a 375° oven.
